WEBVTT

1
00:01:09.151 --> 00:01:13.151
<font color="#ff8000">Subtiltles by Prospero</font>
<font color="#00ff00">prospero.13t@gmail.com</font>

2
00:02:54.228 --> 00:02:56.190
They've killed the boy!

3
00:02:58.959 --> 00:03:01.189
They've killed young Paolo!

4
00:03:03.197 --> 00:03:05.791
They've killed your son Paolo!

5
00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:07.767
Murderers!

6
00:03:23.184 --> 00:03:24.979
My son...

7
00:04:09.163 --> 00:04:11.188
All my respect. Don Ciccio.

8
00:04:14.266 --> 00:04:15.566
Don Ciccio!

9
00:04:15.636 --> 00:04:19.364
You killed my husband because
he wouldn't give in to you.

10
00:04:20.274 --> 00:04:22.975
And his oldest son Paolo...

11
00:04:23.344 --> 00:04:25.572
...because he swore revenge.

12
00:04:26.213 --> 00:04:28.615
But Vito is only nine.

13
00:04:29.139 --> 00:04:30.839
and dumb-witted.

14
00:04:31.585 --> 00:04:33.143
He never speaks.

15
00:04:33.254 --> 00:04:35.882
It's not his words I'm afraid of.

16
00:04:36.924 --> 00:04:41.652
He is weak. He couldn't hurt anyone.

17
00:04:42.329 --> 00:04:44.889
But when he grows.
he'll grow strong.

18
00:04:45.065 --> 00:04:48.826
Don't worry. This little boy
can't do a thing to you.

19
00:04:56.176 --> 00:05:00.210
When he is a man.
he'll come for revenge.

20
00:05:01.382 --> 00:05:03.577
I beg you. Don Ciccio.

21
00:05:03.717 --> 00:05:06.015
spare my only son.

22
00:05:06.353 --> 00:05:08.378
He is all I have left.

23
00:05:08.722 --> 00:05:12.185
I swear to God he'll
never do you any harm.

24
00:05:12.526 --> 00:05:14.385
Spare him!

25
00:05:19.243 --> 00:05:20.543
No.

26
00:05:23.037 --> 00:05:24.834
Vito. run!

27
00:05:24.939 --> 00:05:26.907
Move and I'll kill him!

28
00:05:27.007 --> 00:05:29.704
Run. Vito!

29
00:05:32.513 --> 00:05:38.475
Kill him!

30
00:05:42.022 --> 00:05:48.293
Any family who hides the boy
Vito Andolini will regret it!

31
00:05:51.732 --> 00:05:54.262
You understand? Yes or no?

32
00:05:57.938 --> 00:06:01.205
Take care and listen to what I'm saying.

33
00:06:01.684 --> 00:06:04.984
Anybody who hides the boy
Vito Andolini is in for trouble!

34
00:06:33.440 --> 00:06:36.773
Vito. we're praying for you!

35
00:06:38.879 --> 00:06:45.180
if anyone is hiding the boy Vito Andolini.

36
00:06:45.686 --> 00:06:48.011
turn him over to us.

37
00:06:48.322 --> 00:06:51.686
Don Ciccio will thank you for it!

38
00:06:52.726 --> 00:06:58.699
It'll be better for the boy.
and better for you!

39
00:07:07.608 --> 00:07:13.840
Any family who hides the boy
Vito Andolini will regret it!

40
00:08:45.739 --> 00:08:47.001
Nurse.

41
00:09:13.400 --> 00:09:14.863
Money?

42
00:09:16.603 --> 00:09:17.827
Interpreter!

43
00:09:24.711 --> 00:09:26.201
Where are you from?

44
00:09:27.481 --> 00:09:29.039
What is your name?
Maria.

45
00:09:33.854 --> 00:09:36.049
What is your name?

46
00:09:37.691 --> 00:09:39.886
Come on. son. What is your name?

47
00:09:43.730 --> 00:09:46.199
Vito Andolini from Corleone.

48
00:09:47.434 --> 00:09:50.026
Corleone. Vito Corleone.

49
00:09:50.671 --> 00:09:52.729
Okay. over there.

50
00:09:54.241 --> 00:09:55.765
Next.

51
00:09:56.544 --> 00:09:57.944
Your name?

52
00:10:04.751 --> 00:10:08.382
Tell him he has smallpox.
Quarantine three months.

53
00:10:18.298 --> 00:10:23.334
Vito Corleone!

54
00:10:25.138 --> 00:10:27.470
Here he is. This is him.

55
00:12:14.414 --> 00:12:16.575
Did you bring the car keys?

56
00:12:19.052 --> 00:12:21.414
Laurie! Laurie!

57
00:12:41.641 --> 00:12:42.835
Mama!

58
00:12:44.911 --> 00:12:46.105
Mama!

59
00:12:48.749 --> 00:12:51.609
Look who is here.
Father Carmelo.

60
00:12:51.651 --> 00:12:53.619
This is Father Carmelo.
our family priest.

61
00:12:53.643 --> 00:12:55.743
I'm Merle Johnson.
Nice to meet you.

62
00:12:56.656 --> 00:12:58.217
Mama.

63
00:12:59.086 --> 00:13:00.271
Here I am.

64
00:13:00.327 --> 00:13:02.190
Constanzia. finalmente

65
00:13:02.195 --> 00:13:03.492
after one week?

66
00:13:03.597 --> 00:13:07.060
I sent the car to the airport
last week to pick you up.

67
00:13:07.701 --> 00:13:08.859
It was chaos.

68
00:13:08.869 --> 00:13:11.099
Anyway. here I am. just one week late.

69
00:13:11.238 --> 00:13:13.768
And this is for my mama!

70
00:13:14.074 --> 00:13:16.008
What is this?
You remember Merle. don't you?

71
00:13:16.109 --> 00:13:17.267
Hello. Mama.

72
00:13:17.277 --> 00:13:19.404
Hello. How are you?
Thank you.

73
00:13:19.846 --> 00:13:21.680
Where is Michael?
I gotta talk to him

74
00:13:21.704 --> 00:13:23.082
and get a few things straight.

75
00:13:23.083 --> 00:13:24.873
and I can't wait on line.

76
00:13:25.485 --> 00:13:27.853
You go see your children first.

77
00:13:28.054 --> 00:13:31.551
And then you worry about waiting
on line to see your brother.

78
00:13:31.690 --> 00:13:33.290
Like everybody else.

79
00:13:38.498 --> 00:13:40.090
Ladies and gentlemen...

80
00:13:41.802 --> 00:13:45.001
A most distinguished guest
would like to say a few words.

81
00:13:45.238 --> 00:13:47.706
Would you please welcome Senator Pat Geary

82
00:13:47.808 --> 00:13:49.407
of the State of Nevada?

83
00:13:49.576 --> 00:13:51.703
And there is Mrs Geary.

84
00:14:02.923 --> 00:14:04.957
Thank you very much
ladies and gentlemen.

85
00:14:05.025 --> 00:14:11.394
This is a very. very happy day
for me and my wife Mrs Geary.

86
00:14:12.232 --> 00:14:15.163
We see Nevada far too seldom.

87
00:14:15.635 --> 00:14:19.098
But particularly today we
can join with old friends.

88
00:14:19.473 --> 00:14:20.665
We can make new friends.

89
00:14:20.707 --> 00:14:24.339
and we help celebrate a
young man's first Communion.

90
00:14:25.145 --> 00:14:31.308
And also to thank that boy's family for
a magnificent contribution to the State.

91
00:14:32.285 --> 00:14:34.413
I have here in my hand a cheque

92
00:14:35.589 --> 00:14:37.687
made out to the university.

93
00:14:38.058 --> 00:14:40.354
and it is a magnificent endowment

94
00:14:40.894 --> 00:14:42.529
in the name of ...

95
00:14:44.008 --> 00:14:46.208
Anthony Vito Corleone.

96
00:14:48.201 --> 00:14:50.566
And the cheque is signed by
that young man's parents.

97
00:14:50.805 --> 00:14:53.305
whom I think we should recognise.

98
00:14:53.944 --> 00:14:56.844
Mike. Pat. Kay. Stand up. please.

99
00:14:57.611 --> 00:14:58.905
Stand up. let the folks see you!

100
00:14:58.912 --> 00:15:01.005
Folks. I want you to join with me

101
00:15:01.114 --> 00:15:07.110
in giving a real Nevada thank you
to Mr and Mrs Michael Corleone!

102
00:15:12.726 --> 00:15:15.723
We also have. as a
special added attraction.

103
00:15:16.029 --> 00:15:17.997
the Sierra Boys Choir.

104
00:15:18.098 --> 00:15:22.033
who have chosen a certain special song

105
00:15:23.069 --> 00:15:26.038
in a special arrangement
to honour their host.

106
00:15:26.139 --> 00:15:27.907
Mr Michael Corleone.

107
00:15:28.575 --> 00:15:29.872
Boys.

108
00:15:46.893 --> 00:15:48.187
Relax.

109
00:15:48.929 --> 00:15:50.954
Okay. fellows. we got that one.

110
00:15:52.666 --> 00:15:54.930
Okay. that's good.

111
00:15:55.035 --> 00:15:58.565
Now. Senator. this is you and Mrs Corleone.

112
00:16:20.360 --> 00:16:21.918
This is my lawyer Tom Hagen.

113
00:16:22.028 --> 00:16:23.222
Senator Geary.

114
00:16:23.396 --> 00:16:26.429
He is the one who arranged this whole
thing through your man Turnbull.

115
00:16:26.633 --> 00:16:28.160
Yes. yes.

116
00:16:28.401 --> 00:16:29.800
Sit down.

117
00:16:33.006 --> 00:16:36.870
Well I was under the impression
that you and I would talk alone.

118
00:16:37.744 --> 00:16:40.235
I trust these men with my life. Senator.

119
00:16:41.014 --> 00:16:43.708
If I were to ask them to leave.
it would be an insuit.

120
00:16:43.717 --> 00:16:44.941
Well.

121
00:16:45.385 --> 00:16:46.783
it's perfectly all right with me.

122
00:16:46.792 --> 00:16:48.871
but I should tell you
that I am a blunt man.

123
00:16:48.877 --> 00:16:51.402
And I intend to speak very frankly to you.

124
00:16:51.758 --> 00:16:57.025
Maybe more frankly than anyone in my
position has ever talked to you before.

125
00:16:57.397 --> 00:17:00.291
The Corleone family done
very well here in Nevada.

126
00:17:00.667 --> 00:17:05.536
You own. or control.
two major hotels in Vegas.

127
00:17:05.705 --> 00:17:07.129
one in Reno.

128
00:17:08.008 --> 00:17:10.442
The licences were grandfathered in.

129
00:17:10.610 --> 00:17:14.606
so there is no problem
with the Gaming Commission.

130
00:17:15.649 --> 00:17:18.675
Now my sources tell me that

131
00:17:18.785 --> 00:17:21.511
you plan to make a move
against the Tropigala.

132
00:17:22.822 --> 00:17:24.790
They tell me that. within a week.

133
00:17:24.958 --> 00:17:27.053
you're gonna move Klingman out.

134
00:17:27.927 --> 00:17:29.724
That's quite an expansion.

135
00:17:29.896 --> 00:17:33.923
However. it will leave you
with one little technical problem.

136
00:17:36.436 --> 00:17:39.301
The licence will still be
in Klingman's name.

137
00:17:40.507 --> 00:17:42.270
Turnbull is a good man.

138
00:17:42.375 --> 00:17:45.173
Yeah. well. let's cut out the bullshit.

139
00:17:45.311 --> 00:17:48.371
I don't want to spend anymore
time here than I have to.

140
00:17:48.548 --> 00:17:50.407
You can have the licence.

141
00:17:50.850 --> 00:17:53.385
The price is 250.000 dollars.

142
00:17:53.887 --> 00:17:56.685
Plus a monthly payment
of 5% of the gross

143
00:17:56.790 --> 00:18:00.657
of all four hotels. Mr Corleone.

144
00:18:04.798 --> 00:18:08.559
Now the price for the licence
is less than 20.000 dollars.

145
00:18:09.035 --> 00:18:10.900
Am I right?
That's right.

146
00:18:12.105 --> 00:18:14.969
Now why would I ever consider
paying more than that?

147
00:18:14.974 --> 00:18:17.242
Because I intend to squeeze you.

148
00:18:17.911 --> 00:18:19.936
I don't like your kind of people.

149
00:18:20.547 --> 00:18:25.511
I don't like to see you come out
to this clean country in oily hair.

150
00:18:25.635 --> 00:18:27.835
dressed up in those silk suits

151
00:18:28.688 --> 00:18:31.924
and try to pass yourselves
off as decent Americans.

152
00:18:32.592 --> 00:18:34.121
I'll do business with you.

153
00:18:34.216 --> 00:18:37.677
but the fact is that I
despise your masquerade.

154
00:18:38.698 --> 00:18:41.599
the dishonest way you pose yourselves.

155
00:18:41.768 --> 00:18:44.134
yourself and your whole fucking family.

156
00:18:51.678 --> 00:18:52.904
Senator.

157
00:18:54.481 --> 00:18:56.749
we're both part of the same hypocrisy.

158
00:18:58.985 --> 00:19:02.580
But never think it applies to my family.

159
00:19:03.089 --> 00:19:04.924
All right. all right.

160
00:19:05.748 --> 00:19:08.048
Some people have to play little games.

161
00:19:09.662 --> 00:19:11.061
You play yours.

162
00:19:13.833 --> 00:19:17.525
So let's just say that you'll pay me
because it's in your interest to pay me.

163
00:19:18.505 --> 00:19:21.497
But I want your answer and
the money by noon tomorrow.

164
00:19:21.674 --> 00:19:25.811
One more thing. Don't you
contact me again. ever.

165
00:19:26.446 --> 00:19:29.247
From now on you deal with Turnbull.

166
00:19:29.649 --> 00:19:32.311
Open that door. son.
Senator.

167
00:19:32.886 --> 00:19:35.382
you can have my answer now if you like.

168
00:19:37.490 --> 00:19:39.481
My offer is this:

169
00:19:40.360 --> 00:19:41.884
Nothing.

170
00:19:43.663 --> 00:19:45.858
Not even the fee for the gaming licence.

171
00:19:45.965 --> 00:19:49.265
which I would appreciate if
you would put up personally.

172
00:19:54.641 --> 00:19:56.472
Good afternoon. gentlemen.

173
00:19:59.779 --> 00:20:02.373
Ladies! I didn't know you were out here.

174
00:20:02.482 --> 00:20:04.177
Honey. we have to go
we're 30 minutes late.

175
00:20:04.250 --> 00:20:05.839
Really? I'm sorry.

176
00:20:05.863 --> 00:20:07.563
Mrs. Corleone. I've been delighted.

177
00:20:07.921 --> 00:20:10.046
It was our pleasure.
Thank you so much.

178
00:20:10.056 --> 00:20:11.680
It was wonderful talking to you.

179
00:20:56.402 --> 00:20:57.460
Fredo!

180
00:20:57.570 --> 00:21:01.462
Fredo. you son of a bitch.
you look great!

181
00:21:01.841 --> 00:21:03.536
Frank Pentangeli!

182
00:21:03.710 --> 00:21:06.609
I thought you was never
coming out west. you big bum!

183
00:21:07.881 --> 00:21:10.475
I gotta check on my boys.

184
00:21:10.583 --> 00:21:13.279
Fredo. what's with the food around here?

185
00:21:13.386 --> 00:21:14.516
What's the matter?
A kid

186
00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:16.221
comes up to me in a
white jacket. gives me

187
00:21:16.222 --> 00:21:19.680
a Ritz cracker and chopped
liver. he says "canapes".

188
00:21:19.792 --> 00:21:25.424
I said. "Can of peas. my ass. That's
a Ritz cracker and chopped liver!"

189
00:21:28.245 --> 00:21:30.045
Bring out the peppers and sardines!

190
00:21:32.038 --> 00:21:35.633
Seeing you reminds me of
New York. the old days!

191
00:21:35.742 --> 00:21:38.939
Fredo. you remember Willi Cicci who

192
00:21:39.045 --> 00:21:41.448
was with old man Clemenza in Brooklyn?

193
00:21:42.772 --> 00:21:44.049
Yeah. look here!

194
00:21:44.050 --> 00:21:46.610
We were all upset
about that. Frankie.

195
00:21:47.120 --> 00:21:48.382
Heart attack?

196
00:21:48.488 --> 00:21:50.180
No. that was no heart attack.

197
00:21:50.189 --> 00:21:53.124
That's what I'm here

198
00:21:53.226 --> 00:21:55.194
to see your brother Mike about.

199
00:21:55.495 --> 00:21:58.387
But what's with him?
What do you mean?

200
00:21:58.631 --> 00:22:02.032
I mean what do I have to?
Get a letter of introduction

201
00:22:02.135 --> 00:22:03.525
to get a sit-down?

202
00:22:04.170 --> 00:22:06.161
You can't get in to see Mike?

203
00:22:06.272 --> 00:22:08.740
He's got me waiting in a lobby!

204
00:22:12.211 --> 00:22:13.508
Johnny Ola.

205
00:22:13.613 --> 00:22:15.012
Al Neri.

206
00:22:20.920 --> 00:22:22.815
Do you know my lawyer
Tom Hagen? Johny Ola.

207
00:22:22.907 --> 00:22:25.865
Sure. I remember Tom from the old days.

208
00:22:26.292 --> 00:22:28.959
Rocco... What's this?

209
00:22:29.362 --> 00:22:31.296
It's an orange from Miami.

210
00:22:32.131 --> 00:22:35.200
Why don't you take care of Johnny's men.
They look like they might be hungry.

211
00:22:35.201 --> 00:22:36.325
Johnny?

212
00:22:36.962 --> 00:22:38.262
Sit down.

213
00:22:39.372 --> 00:22:40.734
Tom isn't gonna sit in
with us. Johny.

214
00:22:40.740 --> 00:22:43.208
He only handles specific
areas of the family business.

215
00:22:43.232 --> 00:22:44.409
Tom.

216
00:22:44.410 --> 00:22:45.809
Sure. Mike.

217
00:22:50.583 --> 00:22:52.107
What are you drinking. Johnny?

218
00:22:52.552 --> 00:22:53.846
Anisette.

219
00:22:54.055 --> 00:22:55.255
Anisette.

220
00:22:59.092 --> 00:23:01.424
If you need anything Mike.
I'll be outside. alright?

221
00:23:01.561 --> 00:23:03.586
Just tell Rocco we're waiting. Tom.

222
00:23:09.602 --> 00:23:12.127
I just left Mr Roth in Miami.

223
00:23:12.238 --> 00:23:13.398
How is his health?

224
00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:15.207
It's not good.

225
00:23:16.776 --> 00:23:19.574
Is there anything I can do.
anything I can send?

226
00:23:19.679 --> 00:23:23.982
He appreciates your concern.
Michael. and your respect.

227
00:23:24.684 --> 00:23:28.643
That casino you are interested in. the
registered owners are Jacob Lawrence.

228
00:23:28.755 --> 00:23:31.446
Allan Barclay. both
Beverly Hills attorneys.

229
00:23:31.958 --> 00:23:34.984
The real owners are the old
Lakeville Road group from Cleveland.

230
00:23:35.094 --> 00:23:36.756
and our friend in Miami.

231
00:23:37.865 --> 00:23:39.650
Meyer Klingman runs the store.

232
00:23:39.766 --> 00:23:41.961
He owns a piece of it
too. he does alright.

233
00:23:42.068 --> 00:23:43.567
but I've been instructed to tell you

234
00:23:43.569 --> 00:23:45.264
that if you move Klingman out.

235
00:23:45.371 --> 00:23:47.896
our friend in Miami will go along.

236
00:23:50.209 --> 00:23:51.972
Thatt's very kind of him.

237
00:23:52.311 --> 00:23:55.212
You tell him it's greatly appreciated.

238
00:23:55.815 --> 00:23:59.342
Hyman Roth always makes
money for his partners.

239
00:24:01.421 --> 00:24:02.752
One by one.

240
00:24:02.855 --> 00:24:04.550
our old friends are gone.

241
00:24:05.324 --> 00:24:06.689
Death

242
00:24:07.093 --> 00:24:08.754
natural or not.

243
00:24:08.861 --> 00:24:11.362
prison. deported...

244
00:24:12.932 --> 00:24:15.298
Only Hyman Roth is the only one left.

245
00:24:15.401 --> 00:24:18.093
because he always made
money for his partners.

246
00:24:20.006 --> 00:24:21.405
I can't believe it!

247
00:24:21.507 --> 00:24:23.338
Out of 30 professional musicians.

248
00:24:23.443 --> 00:24:25.809
there isn't one italian in.
in the group here!

249
00:24:25.912 --> 00:24:28.437
Come. let's have a tarantella!
Come on!

250
00:24:34.287 --> 00:24:36.653
You! Up. clarinet up. up!

251
00:24:45.898 --> 00:24:47.297
Questa mano!

252
00:24:48.734 --> 00:24:50.258
Questa mano!

253
00:24:56.476 --> 00:24:58.837
What the hell have we here?

254
00:25:10.289 --> 00:25:11.886
I'll see my sister alone.

255
00:25:12.725 --> 00:25:15.456
It concerns me too.
Is it okay. Mike. if I stay?

256
00:25:16.129 --> 00:25:17.562
How are you. honey?

257
00:25:17.697 --> 00:25:19.990
You met Merle. he
was with me in Vegas.

258
00:25:20.633 --> 00:25:22.195
I saw him with you.

259
00:25:22.401 --> 00:25:24.100
Could I have a drink or something??

260
00:25:27.940 --> 00:25:30.465
Al. would you please get him a drink!

261
00:25:32.545 --> 00:25:35.905
We're going to Europe next week.
I'd like to book passage on the Queen.

262
00:25:36.253 --> 00:25:39.531
So what do you come to me for?
Why don't you go to a travel agent?

263
00:25:39.552 --> 00:25:41.247
We're getting married first.

264
00:25:50.329 --> 00:25:52.294
The ink on your divorce isn't dry yet.

265
00:25:52.298 --> 00:25:53.963
and you're getting married?

266
00:25:56.736 --> 00:25:58.931
You see your children on weekends.

267
00:25:59.438 --> 00:26:02.737
You know your oldest boy. Victor was
picked up in Reno for some petty theft

268
00:26:02.975 --> 00:26:04.640
you don't even know about.
Michael!

269
00:26:04.710 --> 00:26:06.778
You fly around the world with
men who don't care for you.

270
00:26:06.812 --> 00:26:09.210
and use you ike a whore!
You're not my father!

271
00:26:09.215 --> 00:26:10.609
So what do you come to me for?

272
00:26:10.650 --> 00:26:12.212
Because I need money.

273
00:26:25.298 --> 00:26:27.797
Connie. Connie. Connie...

274
00:26:34.707 --> 00:26:36.472
I wanna be reasonable with you.

275
00:26:38.311 --> 00:26:41.408
Now why don't you stay
with us. with the family?

276
00:26:42.181 --> 00:26:44.741
You can live on here on
the estate with your kids.

277
00:26:45.017 --> 00:26:46.575
You won't be deprived of anything.

278
00:26:46.599 --> 00:26:48.399
and you can have everything you want.

279
00:26:53.125 --> 00:26:54.251
I don't know this Merle.

280
00:26:54.427 --> 00:26:56.387
I don't know what he does.

281
00:26:56.781 --> 00:26:58.581
I don't know what he lives on.

282
00:27:00.166 --> 00:27:02.662
Now why don't you tell him that
marriage is out of the question and

283
00:27:02.686 --> 00:27:04.486
you don't want to see him anymore?

284
00:27:05.471 --> 00:27:07.496
He'll understand. believe me.

285
00:27:15.748 --> 00:27:17.047
Connie.

286
00:27:19.719 --> 00:27:21.346
if you don't listen to me.

287
00:27:22.255 --> 00:27:23.779
and marry this man...

288
00:27:28.361 --> 00:27:29.953
...you'll disappoint me.

289
00:28:02.195 --> 00:28:03.859
Famiglia!

290
00:28:04.283 --> 00:28:06.083
Cent' anni!

291
00:28:06.799 --> 00:28:08.193
What's "Chen dannay"?

292
00:28:09.235 --> 00:28:12.204
"Cent' anni". It means 100 years.

293
00:28:12.405 --> 00:28:15.101
It means we should all
live happily for 100 years.

294
00:28:15.207 --> 00:28:16.506
The family.

295
00:28:16.676 --> 00:28:18.539
It would be true if my father were alive.

296
00:28:18.678 --> 00:28:19.975
Connie.

297
00:28:22.281 --> 00:28:23.370
Merle.

298
00:28:23.416 --> 00:28:25.381
you've met my sister-in-law Deanna.

299
00:28:26.419 --> 00:28:28.108
Fredo's wife.
My pleasure.

300
00:28:28.207 --> 00:28:29.907
How do you do?
My pleasure.

301
00:28:32.135 --> 00:28:33.635
What did she mean by that?

302
00:28:34.160 --> 00:28:36.185
Michael. excuse me.

303
00:28:37.229 --> 00:28:39.168
With all respect.

304
00:28:39.437 --> 00:28:42.137
I didn't come here to eat dinner!

305
00:28:43.402 --> 00:28:45.070
I know. I know.

306
00:29:15.601 --> 00:29:17.899
What's the matter?
I just want to dance!

307
00:29:18.037 --> 00:29:20.603
Dancing is one thing.
You're falling all over the floor.

308
00:29:20.604 --> 00:29:22.116
I know what's the matter with you.

309
00:29:22.141 --> 00:29:24.436
You're just jealous
because he is a real man!

310
00:29:24.510 --> 00:29:27.078
I swear to God. Deanna. I'm
gonna belt you right in the teeth.

311
00:29:27.146 --> 00:29:29.137
You couldn't belt your mama!

312
00:29:29.559 --> 00:29:32.959
You know something. these daigos
are crazy when it comes to their wives.

313
00:29:33.185 --> 00:29:35.745
Michael says that if you
can't take care of this.

314
00:29:35.988 --> 00:29:37.455
I have to.

315
00:29:38.557 --> 00:29:39.917
Maybe you'd better.

316
00:29:40.092 --> 00:29:41.491
Never marry a Wop.

317
00:29:41.627 --> 00:29:43.288
They treat their wives like shit!

318
00:29:43.496 --> 00:29:44.986
I didn't mean to say Wop.

319
00:29:45.765 --> 00:29:47.065
Stop now!

320
00:29:47.710 --> 00:29:49.510
What are you doing to me?

321
00:29:52.563 --> 00:29:53.763
Fredo!

322
00:29:54.028 --> 00:29:55.818
I can't control her. Mikey.

323
00:29:55.875 --> 00:29:58.533
You're my brother. Frdeo.
You don't have to apologise to me.

324
00:30:02.915 --> 00:30:04.576
Clemenza promised the Rosato brothers

325
00:30:04.650 --> 00:30:06.982
three territories in the
Bronx after he died.

326
00:30:07.052 --> 00:30:08.179
You took over

327
00:30:08.203 --> 00:30:09.853
and you didn't give it to them.
I welched.

328
00:30:09.922 --> 00:30:13.153
You welched!
Yeah. Clemenza promised them lu cazzo.

329
00:30:13.259 --> 00:30:15.124
Clemenza promised them nothing.

330
00:30:15.227 --> 00:30:17.821
He hated those son of a
bitches more than I do.

331
00:30:17.997 --> 00:30:20.022
Frankie. they feel cheated.

332
00:30:20.132 --> 00:30:24.262
Michael. you're sitting high
up in the Sierra Mountains

333
00:30:24.370 --> 00:30:26.600
and you're drinking...
What's he drinking?

334
00:30:26.672 --> 00:30:27.761
Champagne.

335
00:30:27.785 --> 00:30:29.707
...Champagne cocktails.

336
00:30:29.708 --> 00:30:31.300
and passing judgement on

337
00:30:31.410 --> 00:30:33.100
how I run my family.

338
00:30:33.546 --> 00:30:38.006
Your family is still called Corleone...

339
00:30:38.451 --> 00:30:41.750
...and you should always respect the family affairs.

340
00:30:41.854 --> 00:30:45.688
My family doesn't eat here.
doesn't eat in Las Vegas.

341
00:30:45.825 --> 00:30:47.850
and doesn't eat in Miami

342
00:30:47.960 --> 00:30:49.587
with Hyman Roth!

343
00:30:56.302 --> 00:31:00.170
You're a good old man. and I like you.

344
00:31:00.940 --> 00:31:03.500
You were loyal to my father for years.

345
00:31:04.677 --> 00:31:08.773
The Rosato brothers are taking hostages.

346
00:31:09.882 --> 00:31:12.851
Mike. they spit right in my face.

347
00:31:13.352 --> 00:31:15.977
all because they're backed
up by that Jew in Miami.

348
00:31:16.055 --> 00:31:17.215
I know.

349
00:31:17.423 --> 00:31:18.913
That's why I don't want them touched.

350
00:31:19.024 --> 00:31:20.614
You don't want 'em touched.
No.

351
00:31:20.693 --> 00:31:22.358
I want you to be fair with them.

352
00:31:22.828 --> 00:31:24.796
You want me to be fair with them?

353
00:31:25.498 --> 00:31:29.628
Tom. how can you be fair to animals?
Tom. for Crissakes.

354
00:31:29.802 --> 00:31:32.100
listen. They recruit spics.

355
00:31:32.204 --> 00:31:34.069
they recruit niggers.

356
00:31:34.240 --> 00:31:38.142
They do violence in their
grandmothers' neighbourhoods!

357
00:31:38.244 --> 00:31:41.844
And I tell you everything
with them is whores!

358
00:31:43.168 --> 00:31:44.616
Junk. dope!

359
00:31:44.617 --> 00:31:46.847
And they leave the gambling to last.

360
00:31:47.152 --> 00:31:49.017
I want to run my family

361
00:31:49.121 --> 00:31:50.383
without you on my back.

362
00:31:50.523 --> 00:31:53.988
I want those Rosatos brothers dead!
No.

363
00:31:54.226 --> 00:31:55.523
Morte.

364
00:32:01.133 --> 00:32:04.296
Now I have business that's
important with Hyman Roth.

365
00:32:04.470 --> 00:32:06.501
I don't want it disturbed.

366
00:32:07.873 --> 00:32:11.267
Then you give your loyaity to
a Jew before your own blood.

367
00:32:13.979 --> 00:32:15.379
Come on. Frankie.

368
00:32:15.414 --> 00:32:18.039
You know my father did
business with Hyman Roth.

369
00:32:18.117 --> 00:32:19.411
He respected him.

370
00:32:19.485 --> 00:32:21.715
Your father did business with Hyman Roth.

371
00:32:21.887 --> 00:32:24.321
your father respected Hyman Roth.

372
00:32:24.423 --> 00:32:27.221
but your father never trusted Hyman Roth

373
00:32:27.393 --> 00:32:30.328
or his Sicilian messenger boy Johnny Ola.

374
00:32:30.429 --> 00:32:37.494
You'll have to excuse me.
I'm tired. and I'm a little drunk!

375
00:32:38.671 --> 00:32:41.071
I want everybody here to know.

376
00:32:41.240 --> 00:32:44.038
there is not gonna be no trouble from me!

377
00:32:44.276 --> 00:32:45.971
Don Corleone.

378
00:32:46.378 --> 00:32:48.608
Cicci. the door.

379
00:32:56.655 --> 00:32:58.479
You want him to leave now?

380
00:33:01.327 --> 00:33:03.054
Let him go back to New York.

381
00:33:03.128 --> 00:33:04.920
I've already made my plans.

382
00:33:06.699 --> 00:33:08.997
The old man had too much wine.

383
00:33:13.839 --> 00:33:15.101
It's late.

384
00:33:27.786 --> 00:33:29.078
How is the baby?

385
00:33:29.888 --> 00:33:31.515
Sleeping inside me.

386
00:33:32.858 --> 00:33:34.323
Does it feel like a boy?

387
00:33:34.326 --> 00:33:37.193
Yes. it does. Michael.

388
00:33:39.798 --> 00:33:40.956
Kay?

389
00:33:41.767 --> 00:33:43.894
I'm sorry about all the people today.

390
00:33:44.403 --> 00:33:48.032
Bad timing. It couldn't be helped. though.

391
00:33:48.641 --> 00:33:51.437
It made me think of what you once told me:

392
00:33:53.979 --> 00:33:58.143
"in five years the Corleone family
will be completely legitimate."

393
00:33:58.317 --> 00:34:00.615
That was seven years ago.

394
00:34:03.589 --> 00:34:04.954
I know.

395
00:34:05.791 --> 00:34:08.419
I'm trying. darling.

396
00:35:11.256 --> 00:35:12.621
Did you see this?

397
00:35:27.840 --> 00:35:29.808
Why are the drapes open?

398
00:35:57.503 --> 00:35:59.403
Kay. are you all right?

399
00:35:59.505 --> 00:36:01.166
Are you hit?
No.

400
00:36:04.243 --> 00:36:05.938
It's over.

401
00:36:08.580 --> 00:36:10.605
Stop! Stop!

402
00:36:11.884 --> 00:36:13.977
Halt!

403
00:36:24.596 --> 00:36:25.927
They're still on the property.

404
00:36:26.031 --> 00:36:28.090
Please. Michael stay inside.

405
00:36:28.333 --> 00:36:29.391
Keep them alive.

406
00:36:29.468 --> 00:36:32.232
We'll try.
Rocco. alive!

407
00:36:33.505 --> 00:36:34.870
Stay by the door.

408
00:37:55.254 --> 00:37:56.482
Yeah. come in.

409
00:38:04.096 --> 00:38:05.529
Mike. are you all right?

410
00:38:05.631 --> 00:38:07.326
Yeah.

411
00:38:11.169 --> 00:38:13.403
There is a lot I can't tell you. Tom.

412
00:38:15.674 --> 00:38:17.705
And I know that's upset you in the past.

413
00:38:17.729 --> 00:38:19.329
A little.
Yeah.

414
00:38:20.178 --> 00:38:24.109
You felt it was because of
some lack of trust or confidence.

415
00:38:25.517 --> 00:38:26.950
But it is...

416
00:38:27.052 --> 00:38:30.488
it's because I admire
you and I love you.

417
00:38:30.589 --> 00:38:33.057
that I kept things secret from you.

418
00:38:35.093 --> 00:38:39.189
That's why at his moment you're
the only one I can completely trust.

419
00:38:40.966 --> 00:38:42.399
Fredo?

420
00:38:42.901 --> 00:38:44.935
Well. he's got a good heart.

421
00:38:45.370 --> 00:38:47.895
But he is weak and he is stupid.

422
00:38:48.006 --> 00:38:50.440
and this is life and death.

423
00:38:50.909 --> 00:38:54.276
Tom. you're my brother.

424
00:38:59.952 --> 00:39:05.254
I always wanted to be thought of as
a brother by you. Mikey. A real brother.

425
00:39:07.626 --> 00:39:09.116
I know that.

426
00:39:15.867 --> 00:39:17.596
You're gonna take over.

427
00:39:18.904 --> 00:39:20.594
You're gonna be the Don.

428
00:39:24.076 --> 00:39:26.704
If what I think has happened has happened.

429
00:39:27.412 --> 00:39:29.277
I'm gonna leave here tonight.

430
00:39:30.449 --> 00:39:32.314
I give you complete power. Tom.

431
00:39:32.417 --> 00:39:36.547
Over Fredo and his men.
Rocco. Neri. everyone.

432
00:39:38.223 --> 00:39:41.454
I'm trusting you with the lives of my wife

433
00:39:41.793 --> 00:39:43.317
and my children.

434
00:39:43.662 --> 00:39:45.489
the future of this family.

435
00:39:48.500 --> 00:39:49.762
If we catch these guys.

436
00:39:49.935 --> 00:39:52.162
do you think we'll be able to
find out who is backing them?

437
00:39:52.170 --> 00:39:53.931
We won't catch them.

438
00:39:55.173 --> 00:39:57.801
Unless I'm very wrong.
they're dead already.

439
00:40:00.212 --> 00:40:02.578
They were killed by somebody close to us.

440
00:40:03.615 --> 00:40:05.048
Inside.

441
00:40:05.250 --> 00:40:08.515
Very very frightened that they botched it.

442
00:40:08.754 --> 00:40:10.984
What about your people Rocco
and Neri? You don't think

443
00:40:11.156 --> 00:40:13.421
that they had something to do with this?

444
00:40:16.495 --> 00:40:17.860
You see...

445
00:40:18.030 --> 00:40:20.965
All our people are businessmen.

446
00:40:22.367 --> 00:40:24.961
Their loyaity is based on that.

447
00:40:27.773 --> 00:40:30.173
One thing I learned from Pop...

448
00:40:31.777 --> 00:40:35.941
...was to try to think as
people around you think.

449
00:40:37.215 --> 00:40:39.979
Now on that basis. anything is possible.

450
00:40:42.087 --> 00:40:45.887
Mike. they're dead! Right
outside my window!

451
00:40:46.058 --> 00:40:49.289
I want to get out of here.
They're lying there dead!

452
00:41:00.472 --> 00:41:03.305
Over here! There is two of them.

453
00:41:03.442 --> 00:41:05.169
Looks like they were hired out of New York.

454
00:41:05.177 --> 00:41:06.838
I don't recognise them.

455
00:41:08.113 --> 00:41:10.244
We won't get anything out of them now.

456
00:41:11.016 --> 00:41:12.608
Fish them out.

457
00:41:37.742 --> 00:41:39.505
Alright. get rid of the bodies.

458
00:41:40.045 --> 00:41:41.373
Where is Mike?

459
00:41:41.379 --> 00:41:42.641
Rocco.

460
00:42:13.145 --> 00:42:18.511
Anthony. everything is gonna
be all right. Try to sleep.

461
00:42:34.633 --> 00:42:36.567
Did you like your party?

462
00:42:37.502 --> 00:42:40.733
I got lots of presents.
I know.

463
00:42:41.573 --> 00:42:42.767
Did you like them?

464
00:42:43.108 --> 00:42:46.339
Yeah. I didn't know the
people who gave them to me.

465
00:42:47.579 --> 00:42:49.046
Well. they were friends.

466
00:42:51.249 --> 00:42:53.479
Did you see my present for you?

467
00:42:53.618 --> 00:42:55.185
It was on my pillow.

468
00:42:57.744 --> 00:42:59.244
Anthony.

469
00:42:59.324 --> 00:43:01.690
I'm gonna be leaving
very early tomorrow.

470
00:43:01.860 --> 00:43:06.422
Will you take me?
No. I can't. Anthony.

471
00:43:06.631 --> 00:43:08.462
Why do you have to go?

472
00:43:09.601 --> 00:43:11.398
'Cause I have to do business.

473
00:43:12.337 --> 00:43:14.032
I could help you.

474
00:43:18.944 --> 00:43:20.703
Some day you will.

475
00:43:22.180 --> 00:43:23.647
Get some sleep.

476
00:44:41.226 --> 00:44:44.127
She is really beautiful.
You've got to see her.

477
00:45:04.482 --> 00:45:09.249
Wait till you see her.
Words can't describe her.

478
00:45:18.163 --> 00:45:23.157
I left Naples. I left Mama.

479
00:45:23.335 --> 00:45:26.668
For a no-good tramp!

480
00:45:26.971 --> 00:45:32.466
Now I am in America. in New York.

481
00:45:33.445 --> 00:45:37.905
Alone! Thinking of my mother.

482
00:45:39.284 --> 00:45:41.752
Without news from home.

483
00:45:43.733 --> 00:45:45.133
Enter.

484
00:45:45.223 --> 00:45:47.783
Pepino. a letter from Naples!

485
00:45:50.366 --> 00:45:52.666
Finally. a letter from Naples!

486
00:45:55.100 --> 00:45:58.365
Vito. how do you like my angel?

487
00:45:59.037 --> 00:46:01.232
Isn't she beautiful?

488
00:46:01.339 --> 00:46:02.567
She is very beautiful.

489
00:46:02.841 --> 00:46:04.103
To you. she is beautiful.

490
00:46:04.209 --> 00:46:06.677
For me. there is only my wife and son.

491
00:46:07.178 --> 00:46:09.203
Our dear mother...

492
00:46:11.082 --> 00:46:12.922
...is dead!

493
00:47:08.206 --> 00:47:12.703
We'll go backstage later
and take her out to eat.

494
00:47:17.415 --> 00:47:21.784
Sit down. you bum!

495
00:47:25.890 --> 00:47:29.121
Excuse me. Don Fanucci.

496
00:47:36.167 --> 00:47:38.965
We'll go see her backstage.

497
00:47:41.439 --> 00:47:45.705
Who was that?
The Black Hand.

498
00:48:17.976 --> 00:48:19.739
That's Fanucci. the Black Hand.

499
00:48:19.844 --> 00:48:22.938
We'll talk about it tomorrow.

500
00:48:23.781 --> 00:48:31.085
Tomorrow! Always tomorrow!

501
00:48:31.689 --> 00:48:34.288
You'll pay me today!

502
00:48:40.231 --> 00:48:41.289
Let's go.

503
00:48:42.166 --> 00:48:46.868
Not my daughter!
Let her go!

504
00:48:49.474 --> 00:48:53.236
Take all my money!

505
00:48:59.050 --> 00:49:01.484
Vito. come on.

506
00:49:05.191 --> 00:49:08.994
I know what you're thinking.

507
00:49:09.661 --> 00:49:11.592
You don't know how things are.

508
00:49:11.663 --> 00:49:13.255
Fanucci is with the Black Hand.

509
00:49:13.398 --> 00:49:15.730
Everybody pays him.

510
00:49:15.833 --> 00:49:17.801
Even my father in the grocery store.

511
00:49:17.936 --> 00:49:19.128
If he is Italian.

512
00:49:19.170 --> 00:49:21.331
why does he bother other Italians?

513
00:49:21.439 --> 00:49:23.666
He knows they have nobody
to protects them.

514
00:49:23.708 --> 00:49:27.304
Forget that. Did you like my angel?

515
00:49:28.580 --> 00:49:30.411
If you're happy. I'm happy.

516
00:50:18.630 --> 00:50:20.192
Don't you feel well?

517
00:50:24.736 --> 00:50:26.863
Is your boss treating you all right?

518
00:50:28.239 --> 00:50:29.763
Forget it.

519
00:50:43.821 --> 00:50:45.550
Hey. you speak italian?

520
00:50:51.929 --> 00:50:56.693
Hide this for me! Next
week I'll come and get it!

521
00:51:35.606 --> 00:51:40.742
Greetings. Abbandando.
Meet my nephew.

522
00:51:42.714 --> 00:51:44.947
How is business?

523
00:51:50.688 --> 00:51:53.314
It's good. it's good.

524
00:51:58.596 --> 00:52:03.499
Fanucci is mad. says the
neighbourhood is getting sloppy.

525
00:52:03.668 --> 00:52:08.162
People don't pay on time and
don't pay the full amount.

526
00:52:08.339 --> 00:52:10.739
Says he is been too nice to everyone.

527
00:52:16.080 --> 00:52:18.275
So Fanucci is changing?

528
00:52:18.449 --> 00:52:21.577
Sure. He wants double from everybody.

529
00:52:21.686 --> 00:52:23.850
Even from my father.

530
00:52:26.691 --> 00:52:28.386
I'm a friend. right?

531
00:52:28.559 --> 00:52:32.962
So you'll let him work here?

532
00:52:58.523 --> 00:53:02.287
Vito. I've got some bad news.

533
00:53:05.096 --> 00:53:08.558
I feel rotten having to tell you this.

534
00:53:11.836 --> 00:53:13.400
Fanucci...

535
00:53:14.334 --> 00:53:16.134
He's got a nephew.

536
00:53:21.179 --> 00:53:23.114
And you have to give him my job.

537
00:53:23.138 --> 00:53:26.138
You've always been good to
me ever since I came here.

538
00:53:26.184 --> 00:53:30.446
You looked after me like a father.

539
00:53:30.988 --> 00:53:35.986
I thank you. And I won't forget it.

540
00:53:51.843 --> 00:53:53.035
Vito!

541
00:54:00.418 --> 00:54:01.646
No!

542
00:54:01.752 --> 00:54:05.654
Take this to your family.

543
00:54:05.823 --> 00:54:08.082
Thanks anyway. but please.
I can't accept.

544
00:54:43.261 --> 00:54:45.422
What a nice pear!

545
00:55:08.486 --> 00:55:11.717
I'm Clemenza. You still have my goods?

546
00:55:14.191 --> 00:55:16.625
Did you look inside?

547
00:55:17.929 --> 00:55:21.160
I'm not interested in things
that don't concern me.

548
00:55:31.943 --> 00:55:34.537
A friend of mine has a nice rug.

549
00:55:34.645 --> 00:55:36.740
Maybe your wife would like it.

550
00:55:43.220 --> 00:55:46.678
Sure she would. but
who has money for a rug?

551
00:55:46.791 --> 00:55:52.320
It would be a present. I know
how to return a favour.

552
00:56:00.604 --> 00:56:04.598
Yeah. sure. My wife would like it.

553
00:56:28.899 --> 00:56:33.596
That son of a bitch! He isn't home.

554
00:56:35.139 --> 00:56:38.165
Damn. He didn't even leave the key.

555
00:56:42.179 --> 00:56:44.374
Well. he won't mind.

556
00:56:55.493 --> 00:57:00.055
Come on in. Hey. Vito. come on in!

557
00:57:23.354 --> 00:57:26.185
This is your friend's place?

558
00:57:27.825 --> 00:57:29.793
This is a real palace.

559
00:57:30.194 --> 00:57:31.923
One of the best.

560
00:57:38.536 --> 00:57:40.570
Vito. give me a hand.

561
00:59:37.488 --> 00:59:39.955
Look how pretty it is. Santino!

562
01:02:08.639 --> 01:02:09.936
Come on in.

563
01:02:12.476 --> 01:02:15.677
It's all right. Come on in.
Hyman is in there.

564
01:02:15.728 --> 01:02:18.228
I was just making some lunch.
Would you like a tuna sandwich?

565
01:02:18.515 --> 01:02:19.846
No. thank you.

566
01:02:27.124 --> 01:02:30.423
<i>...pick up of two by Holden.
Second and eight for S. C...</i>

567
01:02:31.562 --> 01:02:32.756
Mr Roth?

568
01:02:33.630 --> 01:02:34.892
Come in. Michael.

569
01:02:37.000 --> 01:02:39.528
Sit down. make yourseif comfortable.

570
01:02:41.505 --> 01:02:43.370
It's almost over.

571
01:02:45.576 --> 01:02:47.203
You following the football game?

572
01:02:48.979 --> 01:02:50.640
Not for a while I haven't.

573
01:02:50.948 --> 01:02:53.412
I enjoy watching football in the afternoon.

574
01:02:53.984 --> 01:02:56.350
One of the things I
love about this country.

575
01:02:56.854 --> 01:02:58.349
Baseball too.

576
01:02:59.089 --> 01:03:03.685
I've loved baseball ever since
Arnold Rothstein fixed the World Series

577
01:03:03.861 --> 01:03:05.353
in 1919.

578
01:03:11.001 --> 01:03:12.935
I heard you had some trouble.

579
01:03:16.240 --> 01:03:17.832
Stupid.

580
01:03:19.143 --> 01:03:21.907
People behaving like that with guns.

581
01:03:24.047 --> 01:03:26.181
Important thing is you're all right.

582
01:03:26.950 --> 01:03:30.681
Good health is the most important thing.

583
01:03:30.954 --> 01:03:33.821
More than success. more than money.

584
01:03:35.492 --> 01:03:37.119
More than power.

585
01:03:51.642 --> 01:03:54.440
I came here because there
is gonna be more bloodshed.

586
01:03:55.612 --> 01:03:57.680
I wanted you to know
about it before it happens.

587
01:03:57.748 --> 01:04:00.246
so that there is no danger
of starting another war.

588
01:04:00.651 --> 01:04:02.414
Nobody wants another war.

589
01:04:03.720 --> 01:04:06.052
Frank Pentangeli came to my home

590
01:04:06.223 --> 01:04:09.488
and he asked my permission to
get rid of the Rosato brothers.

591
01:04:09.660 --> 01:04:11.924
When I refused he tried to have me killed.

592
01:04:12.095 --> 01:04:13.619
He was stupid. I was lucky.

593
01:04:13.730 --> 01:04:15.129
I'll visit him soon.

594
01:04:15.599 --> 01:04:20.696
The important thing is that nothing
interferes with our plans for the future.

595
01:04:20.871 --> 01:04:23.431
Yours and mine.
Nothing is more important.

596
01:04:26.009 --> 01:04:28.807
You're a wise and considerate young man.

597
01:04:29.079 --> 01:04:31.013
And you're a great man. Mr Roth.

598
01:04:32.049 --> 01:04:33.876
There is much I can learn from you.

599
01:04:34.685 --> 01:04:36.880
Whatever I can do to help. Michael.

600
01:04:39.189 --> 01:04:41.783
Excuse me. Lunch.
Come in.

601
01:04:42.259 --> 01:04:43.692
Thank you. my dear.

602
01:04:43.927 --> 01:04:46.594
Honey Bunny. you're
gonna break your eardrums.

603
01:04:47.831 --> 01:04:49.861
Enjoy it.
Thank you.

604
01:04:56.039 --> 01:04:58.173
You're young. I'm old and sick.

605
01:05:00.010 --> 01:05:04.777
What we'll do together in the next
few months will make history. Michael.

606
01:05:05.015 --> 01:05:07.411
History. It's never been done before.

607
01:05:07.885 --> 01:05:11.981
Not even your father would dream
that such a thing could be possible.

608
01:05:14.458 --> 01:05:18.986
Frank Pentangeli is a
dead man. You don't object?

609
01:05:20.564 --> 01:05:22.429
He is small potatoes.

610
01:05:33.377 --> 01:05:34.639
What is up?

611
01:05:38.115 --> 01:05:39.712
We got company?

612
01:05:54.498 --> 01:05:59.936
Michael Corleone is here.
Where is he?

613
01:06:00.103 --> 01:06:04.233
He is in your den. You better hurry.

614
01:06:04.908 --> 01:06:07.133
He's been waiting for haif an hour.

615
01:06:13.750 --> 01:06:15.843
Is something wrong?

616
01:06:19.985 --> 01:06:21.185
Don Corleone.

617
01:06:21.240 --> 01:06:23.107
I wish you would've let
me know you were coming.

618
01:06:23.126 --> 01:06:25.424
I could have prepared
something for you.

619
01:06:25.662 --> 01:06:27.760
I didn't want you to know I was coming.

620
01:06:35.005 --> 01:06:36.697
You heard what happened in my home?

621
01:06:36.707 --> 01:06:38.272
Mike. I almost died myself.

622
01:06:38.308 --> 01:06:40.868
We were all so relieved...
In my home!

623
01:06:44.014 --> 01:06:46.642
In my bedroom where my wife sleeps!

624
01:06:49.753 --> 01:06:52.415
Where my children come
and play with their toys.

625
01:06:53.857 --> 01:06:55.352
In my home.

626
01:07:12.943 --> 01:07:15.810
I want you to help
me take my revenge.

627
01:07:15.912 --> 01:07:18.645
Michael. anything. What can I do?

628
01:07:22.886 --> 01:07:25.414
Settle these troubles with
the Rosato brothers.

629
01:07:26.223 --> 01:07:27.884
Mike. I don't understand. I don't...

630
01:07:27.991 --> 01:07:30.155
Look. I don't have your brain

631
01:07:30.861 --> 01:07:32.123
for big deals.

632
01:07:32.229 --> 01:07:33.719
But this is a street thing.

633
01:07:33.830 --> 01:07:38.727
That Hyman Roth in Miami.
He is backing up those sons of bitches.

634
01:07:39.036 --> 01:07:40.294
I know he is.

635
01:07:40.295 --> 01:07:41.546
So why?

636
01:07:41.571 --> 01:07:44.369
So why ask me to lay down to them. Mike?

637
01:07:49.613 --> 01:07:52.275
It was Hyman Roth that
tried to have me killed.

638
01:07:54.785 --> 01:07:56.252
I know it was him.

639
01:07:57.988 --> 01:07:59.819
Jesus Christ. Mike.

640
01:08:00.424 --> 01:08:02.857
Jesus Christ. look let's get them all.

641
01:08:02.990 --> 01:08:05.314
Let's get 'em all now.
while we got the muscle.

642
01:08:10.600 --> 01:08:13.364
This used to be my father's old study.

643
01:08:14.471 --> 01:08:15.938
It's changed.

644
01:08:17.808 --> 01:08:19.173
I remember there used to be...

645
01:08:20.343 --> 01:08:22.038
a big desk right here.

646
01:08:25.215 --> 01:08:26.977
I remember when I was a kid. Frankie.

647
01:08:27.001 --> 01:08:29.501
We had to be very quiet
when we played near here.

648
01:08:37.794 --> 01:08:41.125
I was very happy that this
house never went to strangers.

649
01:08:42.899 --> 01:08:45.958
First Clemenza took it over. Now you.

650
01:08:48.572 --> 01:08:50.972
My father taught me many things here.

651
01:08:51.374 --> 01:08:52.966
He taught me in this room.

652
01:08:57.080 --> 01:09:00.538
He taught me. "Keep your friends close.

653
01:09:00.784 --> 01:09:02.809
but your enemies closer."

654
01:09:03.253 --> 01:09:06.586
Now if Hyman Roth sees that
I interceded in this thing.

655
01:09:06.757 --> 01:09:08.650
in the Rosato brothers' favour.

656
01:09:09.526 --> 01:09:12.059
he is gonna think his
relationship with me is still good.

657
01:09:15.899 --> 01:09:17.764
That's what I want him to think.

658
01:09:19.035 --> 01:09:20.900
I want him completely relaxed

659
01:09:21.071 --> 01:09:23.362
and confident in our friendship.

660
01:09:23.874 --> 01:09:25.239
Then I'll be able to find out

661
01:09:25.342 --> 01:09:27.970
who the traitor in my family was.

662
01:09:55.267 --> 01:09:56.467
Yeah?

663
01:09:56.807 --> 01:09:58.866
Fredo. this is Johnny.

664
01:09:59.376 --> 01:10:02.140
Johnny Ola. We need some more help.

665
01:10:02.245 --> 01:10:03.542
Johnny?

666
01:10:04.347 --> 01:10:06.815
Jesus Christ. what the hell time is it?

667
01:10:07.517 --> 01:10:08.609
Who is that. honey?

668
01:10:09.052 --> 01:10:10.417
Listen good. Fredo.

669
01:10:10.554 --> 01:10:12.349
What are you calling me here for?

670
01:10:12.355 --> 01:10:13.822
I don't want to talk to you.

671
01:10:13.957 --> 01:10:16.023
Pentangeli set up a meeting
with the Rosato brothers.

672
01:10:16.077 --> 01:10:17.877
Says he is gonna go for their deal.

673
01:10:18.562 --> 01:10:20.996
Will he come alone?
I don't know anything.

674
01:10:21.164 --> 01:10:22.731
You've got me in deep enough already.

675
01:10:22.787 --> 01:10:25.464
Just go along. everything
will be alright. Fredo.

676
01:10:25.872 --> 01:10:28.072
Pentangeli says he is
willing to make a deal.

677
01:10:28.307 --> 01:10:32.239
All we want to know is if he is on the
level. or if he is gonna bring his boys.

678
01:10:32.976 --> 01:10:36.036
You guys lied to me. I don't
want you to call me anymore.

679
01:10:36.146 --> 01:10:38.439
Your brother isn't going
to find out we talked.

680
01:10:38.481 --> 01:10:40.210
I don't know what you're talking about.

681
01:10:51.595 --> 01:10:52.857
Who was that?

682
01:10:53.296 --> 01:10:54.689
Wrong number.

683
01:11:02.447 --> 01:11:03.947
Frank.

684
01:11:04.007 --> 01:11:05.497
I got nobody here.

685
01:11:05.675 --> 01:11:06.901
Wait in the car. Cicc'.

686
01:11:06.910 --> 01:11:08.974
Frankie.
That's okay. Cicc'.

687
01:11:16.720 --> 01:11:18.048
What's this. Rosato?

688
01:11:18.121 --> 01:11:20.146
A lucky C note for our new deal.

689
01:11:23.526 --> 01:11:26.051
Ritchie. Give us a taste.

690
01:11:30.500 --> 01:11:33.731
We were all real happy about
your decision. Frankie.

691
01:11:34.504 --> 01:11:36.094
You are not gonna regret it.

692
01:11:36.273 --> 01:11:38.639
I don't like the C note. Rosato.

693
01:11:38.909 --> 01:11:41.036
I take that as an insuit.

694
01:11:41.711 --> 01:11:44.339
Michael Corleone says hello!

695
01:12:01.264 --> 01:12:04.131
Get his head in.
Close the fucking door!

696
01:12:04.434 --> 01:12:05.828
Your friend the cop...

697
01:12:06.770 --> 01:12:08.936
Hey. Ritch. It's dark in here.

698
01:12:09.472 --> 01:12:11.005
Are you open or closed?

699
01:12:11.074 --> 01:12:13.372
I just came in to clean
up a little. you know?

700
01:12:17.280 --> 01:12:18.713
What's the matter?

701
01:12:19.649 --> 01:12:21.114
Is that something on the floor?

702
01:12:21.184 --> 01:12:24.247
Carmine. no not here!
Anthony!

703
01:12:27.257 --> 01:12:29.917
You open this fucker I'm
gonna blow your head off!

704
01:12:29.941 --> 01:12:31.141
Carmine!

705
01:13:16.773 --> 01:13:18.538
Freddy. good to see you.

706
01:13:21.711 --> 01:13:23.214
How is he?

707
01:13:23.215 --> 01:13:24.713
He is okay.

708
01:13:24.937 --> 01:13:26.437
He is in the back.

709
01:13:30.120 --> 01:13:32.213
Come on. girls! Take a hike.

710
01:13:35.892 --> 01:13:37.287
In this room here.

711
01:13:40.530 --> 01:13:42.225
I want to talk to him alone first.

712
01:13:42.399 --> 01:13:43.693
Come on.

713
01:13:52.842 --> 01:13:54.769
I thought I could help you. Senator.

714
01:13:59.482 --> 01:14:00.744
Hagen?

715
01:14:02.652 --> 01:14:04.679
Listen Hagen. I did not...

716
01:14:04.888 --> 01:14:06.622
I know. it's all right.

717
01:14:06.923 --> 01:14:08.183
I didn't do anything.

718
01:14:08.258 --> 01:14:09.520
It's okay.

719
01:14:10.393 --> 01:14:11.885
You're very lucky.

720
01:14:12.595 --> 01:14:14.863
My brother Fredo operates this place.

721
01:14:15.231 --> 01:14:17.096
He was called before anyone.

722
01:14:18.201 --> 01:14:21.295
Had this happened some place else.
we couldn't have helped you.

723
01:14:25.008 --> 01:14:27.442
When I woke up. I was on the floor.

724
01:14:29.646 --> 01:14:31.614
And I don't know how it happened.

725
01:14:31.714 --> 01:14:33.204
You can't remember?

726
01:14:37.454 --> 01:14:39.149
I passed out.

727
01:14:46.010 --> 01:14:47.410
I'll fix it.

728
01:14:55.805 --> 01:14:57.368
Just a game.

729
01:14:57.674 --> 01:14:59.107
Jesus.

730
01:15:09.152 --> 01:15:10.978
Jesus. Jesus!

731
01:15:16.025 --> 01:15:17.285
Jesus God!

732
01:15:18.762 --> 01:15:20.296
God!

733
01:15:22.765 --> 01:15:25.563
I don't know. and
I don't understand why.

734
01:15:25.735 --> 01:15:26.824
I can't remember.

735
01:15:26.903 --> 01:15:29.565
You don't have to remember.
 Just do as I say.

736
01:15:29.806 --> 01:15:32.104
We putting a call in to your office.

737
01:15:32.275 --> 01:15:33.469
explain

738
01:15:33.610 --> 01:15:35.642
that you'll be there
tomorrow afternoon.

739
01:15:36.379 --> 01:15:40.778
You decided to spend the night at
Michael Corleone's house in Tahoe.

740
01:15:41.202 --> 01:15:42.752
As his guest.

741
01:15:43.153 --> 01:15:46.281
I do remember that she was laughing.

742
01:15:48.024 --> 01:15:49.457
We'd done it before.

743
01:15:50.026 --> 01:15:53.660
and I know that I could
not have hurt that girl.

744
01:15:54.531 --> 01:15:56.126
This girl has no family.

745
01:15:56.399 --> 01:15:58.924
Nobody knows that she worked here.

746
01:15:59.102 --> 01:16:01.032
It'll be as though she never existed.

747
01:16:03.940 --> 01:16:05.931
All that's left is our friendship.

748
01:16:21.624 --> 01:16:22.750
Yes?

749
01:16:22.825 --> 01:16:25.521
I'm sorry. Mrs. Corleone.
we're not to let you through.

750
01:16:26.396 --> 01:16:28.054
I'm just going to the market.

751
01:16:28.131 --> 01:16:30.699
Well. just give us a list. we'll
pick up anything you want.

752
01:16:30.700 --> 01:16:32.031
Whose orders are these?

753
01:16:32.135 --> 01:16:34.032
Mr Hagen's. ma'am.
He is coming over here now.

754
01:16:34.037 --> 01:16:36.899
Alright. well. I'm just going to
have to speak with Mr. Hagen.

755
01:16:42.278 --> 01:16:45.941
I wanted to explain this. but
I had business in Carson City.

756
01:16:46.149 --> 01:16:48.274
Now this is Michael's
request for your safety.

757
01:16:48.351 --> 01:16:50.385
Now. we can send out
for anything you need.

758
01:16:50.453 --> 01:16:52.921
I see. So I'm supposed
to stay in my house?

759
01:16:53.089 --> 01:16:55.316
No. within the compound will be fine.

760
01:16:55.558 --> 01:16:58.024
Tom. I was going to take the
children to New England next week.

761
01:16:58.027 --> 01:16:59.460
That's off.

762
01:16:59.562 --> 01:17:01.493
Am I a prisoner? Is that it?

763
01:17:01.497 --> 01:17:02.928
That's not the way
we look at it. Kay.

764
01:17:02.999 --> 01:17:05.561
All right.Come on. kids. We
are going back to the house.

765
01:17:08.304 --> 01:17:09.464
Joe.

766
01:17:55.985 --> 01:17:58.153
Cuba. Cuba!

767
01:18:38.661 --> 01:18:40.253
Most respected gentlemen.

768
01:18:41.864 --> 01:18:43.991
allow me to welcome to the city of Havana.

769
01:18:46.135 --> 01:18:51.072
I want to thank this distinguished
group of American industrialists...

770
01:18:53.176 --> 01:18:55.269
...for continuing to work with Cuba...

771
01:18:56.879 --> 01:18:59.006
...for the greatest period of prosperity...

772
01:19:00.983 --> 01:19:02.348
...in her entire history.

773
01:19:03.986 --> 01:19:05.146
Mr William Shaw...

774
01:19:06.322 --> 01:19:08.051
...representing the General Fruit Company.

775
01:19:10.059 --> 01:19:11.788
Mr Corngold and Dant...

776
01:19:12.862 --> 01:19:14.887
...of United Telephone and Telegraph Company.

777
01:19:17.033 --> 01:19:18.295
Mr Petty...

778
01:19:18.634 --> 01:19:22.263
...regional Vice President of the
Pan American Mining Corporation.

779
01:19:24.507 --> 01:19:27.032
Mr Robert Allen of South American Sugar.

780
01:19:28.911 --> 01:19:31.539
Mr Michael Corleone of Nevada...

781
01:19:33.082 --> 01:19:36.813
...representing our associates in
tourism and leisure activities.

782
01:19:37.754 --> 01:19:40.848
And my old friend and associate from Florida...

783
01:19:42.825 --> 01:19:44.520
...Mr Hyman Roth.

784
01:19:45.094 --> 01:19:47.059
I would like to take
this opportunity to thank

785
01:19:47.063 --> 01:19:49.293
United Telephone and Telegraph for

786
01:19:49.465 --> 01:19:51.057
their lovely Christmas gift.

787
01:19:55.638 --> 01:19:57.606
A solid gold telephone.

788
01:20:00.410 --> 01:20:02.571
Perhaps you gentlemen would
like to take a look at it.

789
01:20:04.647 --> 01:20:06.274
Mr President?
Yes?

790
01:20:06.449 --> 01:20:10.249
Perhaps you would discuss
the status of rebel activity and

791
01:20:10.353 --> 01:20:12.614
what this can mean to our businesses?

792
01:20:12.688 --> 01:20:14.050
Of course.
Heavy stuff.

793
01:20:14.090 --> 01:20:15.250
I want to assure you that.

794
01:20:15.591 --> 01:20:17.554
although the rebels have mounted

795
01:20:17.625 --> 01:20:19.859
an impressive campaign in Las Villas...

796
01:20:26.135 --> 01:20:28.603
...my staff indicates with assurance

797
01:20:28.704 --> 01:20:33.266
that we'll drive them out of the city
of Santa Clara before the New Year.

798
01:20:36.179 --> 01:20:37.940
I want to put you all at ease.

799
01:20:38.848 --> 01:20:42.841
We will tolerate no guerrillas in
the casinos or the swimming pools.

800
01:21:01.737 --> 01:21:03.602
He said that they're making an arrest.

801
01:21:03.706 --> 01:21:06.231
and in a few minutes he'll let us through.

802
01:21:06.976 --> 01:21:09.069
Johnny...
It 's nothing.

803
01:21:09.245 --> 01:21:12.908
Just some lousy bandits.
The police are cleaning them up.

804
01:21:15.285 --> 01:21:16.946
Viva Fidel!

805
01:21:32.502 --> 01:21:34.299
I hope my age is correct.

806
01:21:34.604 --> 01:21:37.095
I'm always accurate about my age.

807
01:21:38.508 --> 01:21:41.909
Make sure that everybody
sees the cake before we cut it.

808
01:21:45.348 --> 01:21:47.009
I'm very pleased

809
01:21:48.017 --> 01:21:52.681
you're all able to come from such
distances to be with me today.

810
01:21:54.223 --> 01:21:57.192
When a man comes to
this point in his life...

811
01:21:58.494 --> 01:22:01.793
...he wants to turn over the
things he's been blessed with.

812
01:22:02.131 --> 01:22:03.996
Turn them over to friends.

813
01:22:04.100 --> 01:22:07.399
as a reward for the friends he's had.

814
01:22:08.304 --> 01:22:11.796
And to make sure that everything goes well

815
01:22:11.941 --> 01:22:13.499
after he is gone.

816
01:22:13.743 --> 01:22:15.337
Not for years.
Hear. hear!

817
01:22:16.612 --> 01:22:19.080
Well. we'll see.
The doctors would disagree.

818
01:22:19.181 --> 01:22:20.714
but what do they know?

819
01:22:21.984 --> 01:22:26.747
These are wonderful things
that we've achieved in Havana.

820
01:22:27.223 --> 01:22:30.021
and there is no limit to
where we can go from here.

821
01:22:30.192 --> 01:22:34.856
This kind of government knows how
to help business. to encourage it.

822
01:22:34.964 --> 01:22:39.094
The hotels here are bigger and swankier

823
01:22:39.201 --> 01:22:42.102
than any of the rug joints
we've put in Vegas.

824
01:22:42.204 --> 01:22:45.173
And we can thank our friends
in the Cuban government.

825
01:22:45.308 --> 01:22:49.972
which has put up half the cash with
the Teamsters. on a dollar for dollar basis.

826
01:22:50.079 --> 01:22:52.843
and has relaxed restrictions on imports.

827
01:22:53.015 --> 01:22:54.073
What I'm saying is

828
01:22:54.150 --> 01:22:57.244
that we have now what
we have always needed:

829
01:22:57.386 --> 01:22:59.980
Real partnership with a government.

830
01:23:00.423 --> 01:23:01.685
Smaller piece.

831
01:23:03.125 --> 01:23:05.685
You all know Michael Corleone

832
01:23:05.861 --> 01:23:07.852
and we all remember his father.

833
01:23:08.064 --> 01:23:11.727
At the time of my retirement. or death.

834
01:23:11.901 --> 01:23:16.201
I turn over all my interests
in the Havana operation

835
01:23:16.372 --> 01:23:17.805
to his control.

836
01:23:17.907 --> 01:23:19.199
But...

837
01:23:19.942 --> 01:23:22.040
all of you will share.

838
01:23:22.411 --> 01:23:25.278
The Nationale will go to
the Lakeville Road Boys.

839
01:23:25.881 --> 01:23:29.112
the Capri to the Corleone family.

840
01:23:29.218 --> 01:23:31.618
the Sevilla Biltmore also.

841
01:23:31.721 --> 01:23:35.282
but Eddie Levine of Newport
brings in the Pennino brothers.

842
01:23:35.391 --> 01:23:38.224
Dino and Eddie. for a piece. And also

843
01:23:38.327 --> 01:23:40.386
to handle the actual casino operations.

844
01:23:40.563 --> 01:23:44.124
And we've saved a piece for
some friends in Nevada

845
01:23:44.300 --> 01:23:47.035
to make sure that things
go smooth back home.

846
01:23:50.039 --> 01:23:52.872
I want all of you to enjoy your cake.

847
01:23:53.042 --> 01:23:55.135
So. enjoy!

848
01:23:55.244 --> 01:23:56.833
Happy birthday!
L'chaim!

849
01:23:59.048 --> 01:24:01.346
I saw an interesting thing happen today.

850
01:24:02.785 --> 01:24:05.948
A rebel was being arrested
by the military police.

851
01:24:06.122 --> 01:24:10.582
Rather than be taken alive. he exploded
a grenade he had hidden in his jacket.

852
01:24:10.760 --> 01:24:14.093
He killed himseif and took a
captain of the command with him.

853
01:24:14.196 --> 01:24:16.924
Right Johnny?
Those rebels. you know. they are lunatics.

854
01:24:17.366 --> 01:24:18.934
Maybe so.

855
01:24:19.258 --> 01:24:20.858
But it occurred to me.

856
01:24:21.417 --> 01:24:23.273
that the soldiers are paid to fight.

857
01:24:23.339 --> 01:24:24.670
the rebels aren't.

858
01:24:24.874 --> 01:24:26.298
What does that tell you?

859
01:24:27.243 --> 01:24:28.676
They can win.

860
01:24:30.946 --> 01:24:33.610
This country has had
rebels for the last 50 years.

861
01:24:33.816 --> 01:24:35.511
It is in their blood.
believe me. I know.

862
01:24:35.685 --> 01:24:37.849
I've been coming here since the 20s.

863
01:24:38.554 --> 01:24:40.246
We were running molasses out of Havana

864
01:24:40.322 --> 01:24:41.846
when you were a baby.

865
01:24:42.458 --> 01:24:44.386
The trucks owned by your father.

866
01:24:46.095 --> 01:24:47.460
Michael...

867
01:24:54.804 --> 01:24:57.668
I'd rather we talked about
this when we were alone.

868
01:25:00.576 --> 01:25:03.170
The two million never got to the island.

869
01:25:09.385 --> 01:25:12.786
I wouldn't want it to get around
that you held back the money.

870
01:25:12.955 --> 01:25:15.521
because you had second
thoughts about the rebels.

871
01:25:21.764 --> 01:25:23.157
Sit down.

872
01:25:24.146 --> 01:25:25.446
Sit down.

873
01:25:32.975 --> 01:25:36.939
If I could only live to see it.
to be there with you.

874
01:25:39.181 --> 01:25:44.016
What I wouldn't give for 20 more years.

875
01:25:45.154 --> 01:25:47.645
Here we are. protected.

876
01:25:47.757 --> 01:25:49.987
Free to make our profits without Kefauver.

877
01:25:50.126 --> 01:25:53.055
the goddamn Justice Department and the FBI.

878
01:25:53.863 --> 01:25:55.387
90 miles away.

879
01:25:55.498 --> 01:25:57.796
partnership with a friendly government.

880
01:25:58.734 --> 01:26:00.234
90 miles.

881
01:26:00.658 --> 01:26:02.258
It's nothing.

882
01:26:03.139 --> 01:26:05.965
Just one small step  looking for a man

883
01:26:06.060 --> 01:26:08.528
that wants to be President
of the United States

884
01:26:09.044 --> 01:26:11.842
and having the cash to make it possible.

885
01:26:12.481 --> 01:26:13.741
Michael.

886
01:26:15.684 --> 01:26:17.749
we are bigger than U.S. Steel.

887
01:26:45.047 --> 01:26:47.709
Mikey. how are you? Okay?

888
01:26:49.318 --> 01:26:51.843
Hi! Freddie Corleone.

889
01:26:52.421 --> 01:26:53.820
Mio frati.

890
01:26:55.424 --> 01:26:57.517
Jesus Christ. what a trip!

891
01:26:57.726 --> 01:27:00.550
the whole time I'm thinking what if
somebody knows what I got in here.

892
01:27:01.263 --> 01:27:02.423
Can you imagine that?

893
01:27:02.498 --> 01:27:05.697
Two million dollars in the
seat next to me in the plane?.

894
01:27:09.939 --> 01:27:12.237
Excuse me.
No. it's okay.

895
01:27:14.043 --> 01:27:15.408
You want to count it?

896
01:27:20.549 --> 01:27:22.446
Mikey. what the hell is going on anyway?

897
01:27:22.918 --> 01:27:24.076
I'm totally in the dark.

898
01:27:24.153 --> 01:27:26.312
The family is making an
investment in Havana.

899
01:27:26.322 --> 01:27:28.422
This is a little gift for the President.

900
01:27:29.725 --> 01:27:33.017
That's great! Havana is great.

901
01:27:34.897 --> 01:27:36.726
It's my kind of town.

902
01:27:38.234 --> 01:27:40.029
Anybody I know in Havana?

903
01:27:40.336 --> 01:27:42.734
Know Hyman Roth. Johnny Ola?

904
01:27:46.008 --> 01:27:49.273
No. I've never met them.

905
01:27:52.314 --> 01:27:54.441
Listen. Mikey. I'm...

906
01:27:54.884 --> 01:27:56.283
I'm kind of...

907
01:28:00.222 --> 01:28:01.746
...kind of nervous from the trip.

908
01:28:01.924 --> 01:28:05.018
Can I get a drink or something?

909
01:28:05.394 --> 01:28:07.662
I thought maybe we'd go out together.

910
01:28:08.631 --> 01:28:11.798
I know a place we can spend
some time together. Okay?

911
01:28:14.236 --> 01:28:17.000
Sometimes I think I should've
married a woman like you did.

912
01:28:17.439 --> 01:28:18.810
Like Kay.

913
01:28:19.634 --> 01:28:21.934
Have kids. Have a family.

914
01:28:24.980 --> 01:28:26.845
For once in my life.

915
01:28:27.449 --> 01:28:31.283
be more like... Pop.

916
01:28:33.656 --> 01:28:35.954
It is not easy to be his son. Fredo.

917
01:28:36.792 --> 01:28:38.157
Not easy.

918
01:28:38.427 --> 01:28:41.624
You know Mama used to tease me.
She'd say. "You don't belong to me."

919
01:28:41.797 --> 01:28:44.067
"You were left on the doorstep by gypsies."

920
01:28:45.056 --> 01:28:46.756
Sometimes I think it is true.

921
01:28:48.437 --> 01:28:50.371
You're no gypsy. Fredo.

922
01:28:51.907 --> 01:28:53.340
Mikey...

923
01:28:53.876 --> 01:28:55.867
I was mad at you.

924
01:29:03.519 --> 01:29:06.181
Why didn't we spend time like this before?

925
01:29:07.256 --> 01:29:08.951
You want a drink. right?

926
01:29:09.124 --> 01:29:10.591
Waiter!

927
01:29:17.366 --> 01:29:18.958
How do you say Banana Daquiri?

928
01:29:19.068 --> 01:29:20.399
Banana Daquiri.

929
01:29:20.502 --> 01:29:22.436
That's it?
That's it.

930
01:29:22.871 --> 01:29:24.600
Uno Banana Daquiri...

931
01:29:27.109 --> 01:29:28.508
...and a club soda.

932
01:29:36.285 --> 01:29:38.810
Senator Geary is flying in from
Washington tomorrow night

933
01:29:38.921 --> 01:29:41.287
with some people. some government people.

934
01:29:41.390 --> 01:29:44.218
I want you to show them
a good time in Havana.

935
01:29:46.996 --> 01:29:49.030
My speciality. right?

936
01:29:49.531 --> 01:29:51.556
Can I trust you with something. Fredo?

937
01:29:51.834 --> 01:29:53.196
Of course. Mike.

938
01:29:56.338 --> 01:30:00.577
Later on in the evening we're all invited
to the Presidential Palace reception

939
01:30:00.676 --> 01:30:02.485
to bring in the New Year.

940
01:30:02.511 --> 01:30:07.343
After it's over. they'll take me
home in a military car. alone.

941
01:30:08.384 --> 01:30:10.011
For my protection.

942
01:30:11.020 --> 01:30:14.649
Before I reach my hotel.
I'll be assassinated.

943
01:30:32.741 --> 01:30:35.510
Who?
Roth.

944
01:30:41.517 --> 01:30:44.179
It was Roth who tried
to kill me in my home.

945
01:30:46.255 --> 01:30:48.189
It was Roth all along.

946
01:30:48.724 --> 01:30:50.658
He acts like I'm his son.

947
01:30:50.759 --> 01:30:52.522
his successor.

948
01:30:53.695 --> 01:30:55.490
But he thinks he is gonna live forever

949
01:30:55.497 --> 01:30:57.124
and wants me out.

950
01:31:01.770 --> 01:31:03.135
How can I help?

951
01:31:03.305 --> 01:31:08.265
You just go along. as though you know
nothing. I've already made my move.

952
01:31:08.377 --> 01:31:09.708
What move?

953
01:31:10.479 --> 01:31:12.777
Hyman Roth will never see the New Year.

954
01:31:30.365 --> 01:31:33.161
Says you have to take it easy. And
he is gonna give you a prescription.

955
01:31:33.168 --> 01:31:34.363
He'll be back tomorrow.

956
01:31:34.462 --> 01:31:36.811
I want my own doctor.
Fly him in from Miami.

957
01:31:36.972 --> 01:31:39.165
I don't trust a doctor
who can't speak English.

958
01:31:40.776 --> 01:31:43.677
Gracias. senor.
Buenas noches.

959
01:31:45.547 --> 01:31:47.481
Honey. go down to the casino.

960
01:31:47.583 --> 01:31:49.275
Well. if you are sure
you are feeling better.

961
01:31:49.284 --> 01:31:50.649
Feel fine.

962
01:31:52.821 --> 01:31:54.288
Play the bingo game.
Okay.

963
01:31:54.623 --> 01:31:57.654
Nice to see you. Mr Paul.
Just make yourself at home.

964
01:31:59.495 --> 01:32:01.326
My sixth sense tells me your brother Fredo

965
01:32:01.497 --> 01:32:03.192
brought a bag full of money.

966
01:32:03.665 --> 01:32:04.923
Where is it?

967
01:32:07.102 --> 01:32:08.467
You're pulling out?

968
01:32:09.505 --> 01:32:10.870
Just want to...

969
01:32:12.207 --> 01:32:13.674
Just want to wait.

970
01:32:17.079 --> 01:32:18.810
How do you feel?

971
01:32:19.334 --> 01:32:20.882
Terrible.

972
01:32:20.883 --> 01:32:24.341
I'd give four million just to be able
to take a piss without it hurting.

973
01:32:25.087 --> 01:32:27.417
Who had Frank Pentangeli killed?

974
01:32:28.490 --> 01:32:30.424
The Rosato brothers.

975
01:32:31.026 --> 01:32:34.223
I know. but who gave the go-ahead?

976
01:32:35.030 --> 01:32:36.622
I know I didn't.

977
01:32:44.706 --> 01:32:47.573
There was this kid I grew up with.

978
01:32:47.743 --> 01:32:49.108
He was younger than me.

979
01:32:49.711 --> 01:32:51.576
Sort of looked up to me. you know.

980
01:32:52.314 --> 01:32:53.581
We...

981
01:32:54.016 --> 01:32:56.041
did our first work together.

982
01:32:56.385 --> 01:32:58.114
Worked our way out of the street.

983
01:32:58.287 --> 01:33:00.983
Things were good.
we made the most of it.

984
01:33:01.390 --> 01:33:07.351
During Prohibition we ran molasses
into Canada. Made a fortune.

985
01:33:07.529 --> 01:33:08.894
Your father too.

986
01:33:11.066 --> 01:33:15.194
As much as anyone. I loved him

987
01:33:15.771 --> 01:33:17.261
and trusted him.

988
01:33:19.675 --> 01:33:23.076
Later on he had an idea

989
01:33:23.412 --> 01:33:26.540
to build a city out of a desert

990
01:33:26.715 --> 01:33:29.973
stop-over for G.I.s
going to the West Coast.

991
01:33:31.386 --> 01:33:34.412
That kid's name was Moe Greene

992
01:33:35.123 --> 01:33:38.191
and the city he invented was Las Vegas.

993
01:33:40.229 --> 01:33:41.958
This was a great man.

994
01:33:42.898 --> 01:33:45.096
A man of vision and guts.

995
01:33:45.400 --> 01:33:48.536
And there isn't even a plaque or a signpost

996
01:33:49.004 --> 01:33:52.462
or statue of him in that town.

997
01:33:53.575 --> 01:33:56.342
Someone put a bullet through his eye.

998
01:33:58.580 --> 01:34:01.540
No one knows who gave the order.

999
01:34:01.883 --> 01:34:04.646
When I heard it. I wasn't angry.

1000
01:34:05.187 --> 01:34:07.312
I knew Moe. I knew he was headstrong.

1001
01:34:07.389 --> 01:34:10.058
Talking loud. saying stupid things.

1002
01:34:11.126 --> 01:34:13.253
So when he turned up dead.

1003
01:34:14.463 --> 01:34:16.156
I let it go.

1004
01:34:17.866 --> 01:34:19.761
And I said to myseif.

1005
01:34:21.069 --> 01:34:23.962
"This is the business we've chosen."

1006
01:34:25.240 --> 01:34:26.832
I didn't ask...

1007
01:34:28.110 --> 01:34:29.739
...who gave the order.

1008
01:34:30.078 --> 01:34:33.139
because it had nothing to do with business.

1009
01:34:41.723 --> 01:34:44.758
That two million in a bag in your room...

1010
01:34:48.497 --> 01:34:50.989
I'm going in to take a nap.

1011
01:34:52.668 --> 01:34:54.133
When I wake.

1012
01:34:55.037 --> 01:34:56.468
if the money is on the table.

1013
01:34:56.538 --> 01:34:58.165
I know I have a partner.

1014
01:34:58.674 --> 01:35:00.705
if it isn't. I know I don't.

1015
01:35:56.765 --> 01:35:58.958
All right. does everybody
know everybody here?

1016
01:35:59.034 --> 01:36:00.667
This is Senator Geary.
You know him.

1017
01:36:00.669 --> 01:36:02.564
How are you. Senator?
Good to see you. Mike.

1018
01:36:02.604 --> 01:36:04.399
I'm glad we could spend
this time together.

1019
01:36:04.406 --> 01:36:06.299
Right. This is Senator
Payton from Florida...

1020
01:36:06.398 --> 01:36:07.683
How ya doing. Mike?

1021
01:36:07.709 --> 01:36:09.233
...Judge DeMalco from New York...

1022
01:36:09.257 --> 01:36:11.145
How do you do. Sir?
Fine. thank you.

1023
01:36:11.246 --> 01:36:12.638
Right. Senator Ream from Maryland...

1024
01:36:12.737 --> 01:36:14.123
Mike. I've been looking forward to it.

1025
01:36:14.149 --> 01:36:15.473
This is Fred Corngold from UTT.

1026
01:36:15.572 --> 01:36:16.826
I know Fred. how are you?

1027
01:36:16.852 --> 01:36:19.320
That Fred does a mean cha-cha-cha.
so watch out later around.

1028
01:36:19.388 --> 01:36:20.477
He does?

1029
01:36:20.560 --> 01:36:22.794
Alright. gentlemen. it's refill time here!

1030
01:36:22.991 --> 01:36:25.218
You might try some of
the local drinks. you know.

1031
01:36:25.260 --> 01:36:26.452
Cuba Libre.

1032
01:36:26.461 --> 01:36:27.723
Pina Colada...

1033
01:36:27.829 --> 01:36:31.390
I think I'll try one of those
redheaded Yolandas.

1034
01:36:31.566 --> 01:36:33.930
That you got! Concusto. you got it.

1035
01:36:33.935 --> 01:36:35.197
Johnny!

1036
01:36:35.537 --> 01:36:37.537
You don't know my brother
Fredo. do you Johnny?

1037
01:36:37.572 --> 01:36:39.367
Johnny Ola. Fredo.

1038
01:36:39.441 --> 01:36:42.410
We never met. Johnny Ola.
Pleasure.

1039
01:36:44.146 --> 01:36:46.580
Gentlemen. to a night in Havana!

1040
01:36:46.748 --> 01:36:48.545
Happy New Year!
Happy New Year!

1041
01:36:48.650 --> 01:36:52.177
Feliz Ano Nuevo!
Happy New Year.

1042
01:36:57.600 --> 01:37:00.000
Never fear. Pat Geary is here.

1043
01:37:03.265 --> 01:37:05.333
Hey. Freddie. why are we standing?

1044
01:37:05.667 --> 01:37:07.066
Everybody stands.

1045
01:37:07.169 --> 01:37:10.229
It's worth it. Watch!
You won't believe this.

1046
01:37:10.405 --> 01:37:11.736
I don't believe it already.

1047
01:37:12.107 --> 01:37:13.231
Fifty dollars. right?

1048
01:37:13.308 --> 01:37:14.898
You got a bet. mister.

1049
01:37:23.418 --> 01:37:25.051
That's him. That is Superman.

1050
01:37:59.221 --> 01:38:01.346
Did I tell you?

1051
01:38:02.858 --> 01:38:04.325
I don't believe it!

1052
01:38:04.459 --> 01:38:05.583
That thing gotta be fake.

1053
01:38:05.660 --> 01:38:08.627
That ain't no fake. That's real.
That's why he is called Superman.

1054
01:38:09.631 --> 01:38:11.322
Hey. Freddy.

1055
01:38:11.800 --> 01:38:13.761
where did you find this place?

1056
01:38:13.785 --> 01:38:16.736
Johnny Ola told me about this place.
He brought me here. I didn't believe it.

1057
01:38:16.805 --> 01:38:18.668
But seeing is believing!

1058
01:38:18.740 --> 01:38:20.230
I see it. but still don't believe it!

1059
01:38:20.342 --> 01:38:21.568
50 bucks. Pat.

1060
01:38:21.610 --> 01:38:23.043
Old man Roth would never come here.

1061
01:38:23.144 --> 01:38:26.040
but old man Johnny knows these
places like the back of his hand.

1062
01:38:26.281 --> 01:38:28.281
Now watch him. he is gonna
break a cracker with it.

1063
01:38:28.350 --> 01:38:31.317
Break a cracker! I want
to see him break a brick.

1064
01:39:53.301 --> 01:39:54.629
Relax. Señor Roth.

1065
01:39:54.636 --> 01:39:56.331
we're taking you to the hospital.

1066
01:40:45.754 --> 01:40:48.052
And in my judgment.
you'll continue to get those

1067
01:40:48.189 --> 01:40:49.483
because I don't believe that

1068
01:40:49.524 --> 01:40:52.593
President Eisenhower
would ever pull out of Cuba.

1069
01:40:52.627 --> 01:40:54.857
not as long as as we have
over one billion dollars

1070
01:40:54.963 --> 01:40:56.521
invested in this country.

1071
01:40:59.734 --> 01:41:02.931
Now the American public
believe in non-intervention.

1072
01:41:03.138 --> 01:41:04.330
Fredo!

1073
01:41:04.806 --> 01:41:06.030
Where are you going?

1074
01:41:06.174 --> 01:41:07.571
I gotta get me a real drink.

1075
01:41:07.642 --> 01:41:08.975
because I can't...

1076
01:42:05.633 --> 01:42:06.927
What kept Mr Roth?

1077
01:42:07.001 --> 01:42:08.566
I understood he was coming.

1078
01:42:09.037 --> 01:42:11.196
Reeves. what is the protocol?

1079
01:42:11.272 --> 01:42:12.803
How long should we stay around?

1080
01:42:12.804 --> 01:42:14.050
I don't know.

1081
01:42:14.075 --> 01:42:15.804
I think a half an hour ought to do it.

1082
01:42:15.910 --> 01:42:18.476
Just long enough
to bring in the New Year.

1083
01:42:32.861 --> 01:42:40.199
It's New Year's Eve! Come on.
just for a minute.

1084
01:43:52.607 --> 01:43:54.140
There is a plane waiting for us

1085
01:43:54.209 --> 01:43:56.905
to take us to Miami in an hour. alright?

1086
01:43:57.011 --> 01:43:58.672
Don't make a big thing about it.

1087
01:44:03.051 --> 01:44:05.042
I know it was you. Fredo.

1088
01:44:05.486 --> 01:44:07.010
You broke my heart.

1089
01:44:08.489 --> 01:44:10.423
You broke my heart!

1090
01:44:50.298 --> 01:44:55.736
Due to serious setbacks to our
troops in Guantanamo and Santiago.

1091
01:44:55.904 --> 01:44:59.738
my position in Cuba is untenable.

1092
01:45:00.174 --> 01:45:05.142
I am resigning from office
to avoid further bloodshed.

1093
01:45:09.851 --> 01:45:14.255
And I shall leave the city immediately.

1094
01:45:18.660 --> 01:45:22.796
I wish all of you good luck.

1095
01:45:23.598 --> 01:45:25.122
Salud!

1096
01:45:27.636 --> 01:45:31.572
Viva la revolucion! Viva Fidel!

1097
01:45:52.827 --> 01:45:54.096
Fredo!

1098
01:45:55.020 --> 01:45:57.020
Come on. Come with me.

1099
01:45:57.365 --> 01:45:59.558
It's the only way out of here tonight.

1100
01:45:59.701 --> 01:46:01.731
Roth is dead. Fredo.

1101
01:46:02.370 --> 01:46:04.062
Fredo. come with me!

1102
01:46:04.138 --> 01:46:06.171
You're still my brother. Fredo!

1103
01:46:33.067 --> 01:46:36.000
Path through. I'm Pat Geary.
United States Senator.

1104
01:47:50.078 --> 01:47:51.311
Al.

1105
01:47:51.735 --> 01:47:53.635
Could you get me a wet towel?

1106
01:48:00.088 --> 01:48:01.655
Kay know I'm back?

1107
01:48:06.894 --> 01:48:08.257
What about my boy?

1108
01:48:08.281 --> 01:48:10.030
Did you get him something
for Christmas?

1109
01:48:10.231 --> 01:48:11.664
I took care of it.

1110
01:48:11.899 --> 01:48:13.461
What was it so I'll know.

1111
01:48:13.701 --> 01:48:17.159
It was a little car with an
electric motor that he can ride in.

1112
01:48:17.271 --> 01:48:18.670
It is nice.

1113
01:48:21.509 --> 01:48:22.899
Thank you. Al.

1114
01:48:24.378 --> 01:48:26.646
Fellas. could you step
outside for a minute?

1115
01:48:44.932 --> 01:48:46.297
Where is my brother?

1116
01:48:47.702 --> 01:48:51.132
Roth got out on a private boat.
He is in a hospital in Miami.

1117
01:48:51.272 --> 01:48:53.497
He had a stroke. but recovered okay.

1118
01:48:54.008 --> 01:48:55.703
Your bodyguard is dead.

1119
01:48:55.877 --> 01:48:57.310
I asked about Fredo.

1120
01:48:58.613 --> 01:49:01.480
I think he got out. He must
be somewhere in New York.

1121
01:49:05.019 --> 01:49:06.316
All right.

1122
01:49:07.688 --> 01:49:09.553
I want you to get in touch with him.

1123
01:49:10.658 --> 01:49:12.248
I know he is scared.

1124
01:49:12.360 --> 01:49:13.552
Tell him everything is all right.

1125
01:49:13.628 --> 01:49:15.892
Tell him I know Roth misled him.

1126
01:49:15.997 --> 01:49:18.295
That he didn't know
they would try to kill me.

1127
01:49:20.168 --> 01:49:21.701
They can come in now.

1128
01:49:22.503 --> 01:49:24.130
There was something else.

1129
01:49:25.173 --> 01:49:26.265
What?

1130
01:49:33.481 --> 01:49:35.506
What? Come on. What?

1131
01:49:37.218 --> 01:49:40.016
Kay had a miscarriage.
She lost the baby.

1132
01:49:52.500 --> 01:49:53.660
Was it a boy?

1133
01:49:53.768 --> 01:49:55.096
Mikey. aftert three
and a haif months...

1134
01:49:55.136 --> 01:49:57.398
Now can't you give me a
straight answer anymore?!

1135
01:49:58.105 --> 01:49:59.697
Was it a boy?

1136
01:50:02.143 --> 01:50:03.770
I really don't know.

1137
01:50:14.889 --> 01:50:17.258
Poor little Fredo.

1138
01:50:17.282 --> 01:50:19.582
He's got pneumonia.

1139
01:51:05.698 --> 01:51:07.598
Go. go! Young man.

1140
01:51:07.723 --> 01:51:12.359
I hear that you and your
friends are stealing goods.

1141
01:51:12.446 --> 01:51:15.006
But you don't even
send a dress to my house.

1142
01:51:15.149 --> 01:51:16.707
No respect!

1143
01:51:16.784 --> 01:51:18.911
You know I've got three daughters.

1144
01:51:19.353 --> 01:51:22.220
This is my neighbourhood.

1145
01:51:22.323 --> 01:51:26.020
You and your friends should
show me some respect.

1146
01:51:26.193 --> 01:51:29.754
You should let me wet my beak a little.

1147
01:51:32.233 --> 01:51:36.294
I hear that you and your friends

1148
01:51:36.671 --> 01:51:39.697
made 600 dollars each.

1149
01:51:39.807 --> 01:51:44.540
If you give me 200 each
for your own protection.

1150
01:51:44.645 --> 01:51:48.046
I'll forget the insuit.

1151
01:51:48.983 --> 01:51:51.679
You young punks have to learn

1152
01:51:51.852 --> 01:51:54.980
to respect a man like me!

1153
01:51:55.690 --> 01:51:58.716
Otherwise the cops will come to your house.

1154
01:51:58.926 --> 01:52:01.451
And your family will be ruined.

1155
01:52:01.996 --> 01:52:04.590
Of course. if I'm wrong
about how much you stole.

1156
01:52:04.732 --> 01:52:07.724
I'll take a little less. And by
less I only mean... 100 bucks less.

1157
01:52:09.537 --> 01:52:11.732
Don't refuse me.

1158
01:52:15.309 --> 01:52:19.370
Understand. paesano?
I understand.

1159
01:52:21.549 --> 01:52:24.484
My friends and I share all the money.

1160
01:52:24.585 --> 01:52:26.883
so I have to talk to them first.

1161
01:52:27.054 --> 01:52:29.420
Tell your friends

1162
01:52:29.523 --> 01:52:33.152
that I don't want a lot.
Just enough to wet my beak.

1163
01:52:36.397 --> 01:52:38.490
Don't be afraid to tell them.

1164
01:52:41.235 --> 01:52:43.328
600 dollars...

1165
01:52:44.572 --> 01:52:46.472
What if we don't pay?

1166
01:52:46.607 --> 01:52:48.905
You know his gang.

1167
01:52:49.009 --> 01:52:50.567
Real animals.

1168
01:52:50.678 --> 01:52:53.841
Fanucci has Maranzalla's personal
blessing to run this neighbourhood.

1169
01:52:53.948 --> 01:52:56.314
including the cops.

1170
01:52:56.450 --> 01:52:58.042
We have to pay him

1171
01:52:58.152 --> 01:53:02.054
200 dollars each. that's it.

1172
01:53:06.227 --> 01:53:07.751
Why do we have to pay him?

1173
01:53:07.862 --> 01:53:10.831
Vito. leave this to us.

1174
01:53:11.665 --> 01:53:14.361
He is one person and we're three.

1175
01:53:14.468 --> 01:53:17.596
He's got guns and we've got guns.

1176
01:53:17.772 --> 01:53:20.900
Why should we give him our money?

1177
01:53:21.008 --> 01:53:24.603
Don't you understand? This is his turf!

1178
01:53:25.179 --> 01:53:30.215
I know two bookies who don't
give anything to Fanucci.

1179
01:53:30.239 --> 01:53:31.384
Who?

1180
01:53:31.385 --> 01:53:35.014
Joe The Greek on Tessimo
Avenue and Frank Pignattaro.

1181
01:53:35.453 --> 01:53:38.153
They don't pay anything to Fanucci.

1182
01:53:38.993 --> 01:53:41.518
If they don't pay Fanucci.

1183
01:53:41.662 --> 01:53:44.597
then somebody else collects for Maranzalla.

1184
01:53:44.698 --> 01:53:48.664
We'll pay him. It is best for everybody.

1185
01:53:49.136 --> 01:53:50.567
Don't worry.

1186
01:54:02.450 --> 01:54:07.786
What I will say stays in this room.

1187
01:54:08.055 --> 01:54:09.920
If you agree.

1188
01:54:10.057 --> 01:54:14.021
give me 50 bucks each to pay Fanucci.

1189
01:54:16.197 --> 01:54:20.190
I guarantee he'll accept what I give him.

1190
01:54:22.670 --> 01:54:24.433
If Fanucci says 200.

1191
01:54:24.572 --> 01:54:26.372
he means it. Vito.

1192
01:54:26.574 --> 01:54:28.439
I'll reason with him.

1193
01:54:29.043 --> 01:54:30.971
Leave it to me.

1194
01:54:34.181 --> 01:54:36.012
I'll take care of everything.

1195
01:54:36.217 --> 01:54:39.020
I never lie to my friends.

1196
01:54:41.288 --> 01:54:44.985
Tomorrow both of you
go and talk to Fanucci.

1197
01:54:45.092 --> 01:54:47.287
He'll ask for the money.

1198
01:54:47.394 --> 01:54:51.758
Tell him you intend to pay
whatever he demands.

1199
01:54:52.199 --> 01:54:53.826
Don't argue with him.

1200
01:54:54.001 --> 01:54:55.796
Then I'll go and get him to agree.

1201
01:54:55.803 --> 01:55:02.800
Just don't get into any arguments.
since he is just as clever as you are.

1202
01:55:02.910 --> 01:55:05.470
How can you get him to take less?

1203
01:55:05.646 --> 01:55:07.737
That's of no interest to you.

1204
01:55:08.249 --> 01:55:11.683
Just remember that I did you a favour.

1205
01:55:16.090 --> 01:55:19.592
Is it a deal?
Yes.

1206
01:56:07.575 --> 01:56:10.043
His family is out of the house.

1207
01:56:10.210 --> 01:56:12.235
Fanucci is alone in the cafe.

1208
01:56:17.418 --> 01:56:20.484
Vito. here is my 50 dollars.
Good luck.

1209
01:56:30.998 --> 01:56:35.230
Vito. are you sure he
is going to go for it?

1210
01:56:36.270 --> 01:56:40.173
I'll make an offer he don't refuse.

1211
01:56:41.275 --> 01:56:42.742
Don't worry.

1212
01:57:15.542 --> 01:57:20.377
It looks like there is...
100 bucks under my hat.

1213
01:57:32.426 --> 01:57:38.456
That's right. Only 100 bucks.

1214
01:57:40.801 --> 01:57:44.635
I'm short of money right now.

1215
01:57:44.738 --> 01:57:50.142
I've been out of work.
so just give me a little time.

1216
01:57:50.244 --> 01:57:53.304
You understand. don't you?

1217
01:58:01.188 --> 01:58:05.022
You've got balls. young man!

1218
01:58:05.793 --> 01:58:09.092
How come I've never heard of you?

1219
01:58:15.269 --> 01:58:18.864
You've got a lot of guts.

1220
01:58:21.742 --> 01:58:25.041
I'll find you some work that pays well.

1221
01:58:35.823 --> 01:58:40.556
No hard feelings. right?

1222
01:58:42.963 --> 01:58:46.760
if I can help you. let me know.
You've done well for yourseif.

1223
01:58:48.969 --> 01:58:51.267
Enjoy the festa!

1224
02:03:25.746 --> 02:03:27.714
What have you got there?

1225
02:06:04.704 --> 02:06:06.305
Michael...

1226
02:06:06.944 --> 02:06:09.544
Your father loves you very much.

1227
02:06:09.568 --> 02:06:11.268
Very much.

1228
02:09:34.638 --> 02:09:37.864
Mr Cicci. from the year
1942 to the present time.

1229
02:09:38.183 --> 02:09:40.879
you were an employee of
the Genco Olive Oil Company?

1230
02:09:41.653 --> 02:09:43.018
That's right.

1231
02:09:44.189 --> 02:09:45.313
But in actuality

1232
02:09:45.390 --> 02:09:48.587
you were a member of the
Corleone crime organisation.

1233
02:09:51.263 --> 02:09:53.991
No. we called it the Corleone family. Senator.

1234
02:09:54.015 --> 02:09:55.666
We called it the family.

1235
02:09:55.667 --> 02:09:57.294
What was your position?

1236
02:09:58.904 --> 02:10:02.032
At first. like everybody else.
I was a soldier.

1237
02:10:02.207 --> 02:10:03.331
What is that?

1238
02:10:03.342 --> 02:10:05.273
A button. you know.
Senator. Come on.

1239
02:10:05.344 --> 02:10:08.142
No. I don't know. Tell me.

1240
02:10:09.414 --> 02:10:11.974
When the boss says "push a button" on a guy.

1241
02:10:12.151 --> 02:10:13.482
I push a button.

1242
02:10:13.652 --> 02:10:14.846
See. Senator?

1243
02:10:15.020 --> 02:10:16.385
Mr Questadt.

1244
02:10:16.822 --> 02:10:19.356
You mean you kill people?
I what?

1245
02:10:19.358 --> 02:10:21.196
You kill people at the...

1246
02:10:21.895 --> 02:10:23.995
at the behest of your superiors.

1247
02:10:28.000 --> 02:10:29.567
Yeah. that's right. Counselor.

1248
02:10:29.635 --> 02:10:34.971
And the head of your
family is Michael Corleone?

1249
02:10:35.073 --> 02:10:37.899
Yeah. Counsellor.
Michael Corleone. right.

1250
02:10:38.277 --> 02:10:40.967
Did you ever get such an order
directly from Michael Corleone?

1251
02:10:42.848 --> 02:10:44.816
No. I never talked to him.

1252
02:10:45.050 --> 02:10:46.347
Mr Cicci.

1253
02:10:46.518 --> 02:10:49.143
could you amplify your
answer a bit please?

1254
02:10:49.221 --> 02:10:50.688
Do what?

1255
02:10:50.789 --> 02:10:52.950
Could you expand on your answer?

1256
02:10:53.058 --> 02:10:57.825
I'm particularly interested in knowing.
was there always a buffer involved?

1257
02:10:58.263 --> 02:11:03.096
Someone in between you and your possible
superiors who gave the actual order.

1258
02:11:03.101 --> 02:11:04.864
Right. yeah a buffer.

1259
02:11:05.103 --> 02:11:07.071
The family had a lot of buffers!

1260
02:11:08.774 --> 02:11:10.808
Mr Cicci. you may find this very amusing.

1261
02:11:10.809 --> 02:11:13.807
but I promise the members
of this committee do not.

1262
02:11:48.280 --> 02:11:53.411
Tell me something. Ma. What
did Papa think. deep in his heart?

1263
02:11:58.123 --> 02:12:01.149
He was being strong.

1264
02:12:03.295 --> 02:12:09.632
Strong... for the family.

1265
02:12:12.271 --> 02:12:17.070
But by being strong for the family...

1266
02:12:22.314 --> 02:12:27.718
...could he lose it?

1267
02:12:29.187 --> 02:12:32.452
You're thinking about your wife.
about the baby you lost.

1268
02:12:32.658 --> 02:12:36.193
But you and your wife can
always have another baby.

1269
02:12:40.966 --> 02:12:46.836
No. I meant... lose the family.

1270
02:12:47.773 --> 02:12:54.235
The family you can never lose.

1271
02:13:00.652 --> 02:13:02.745
Times are changing.

1272
02:13:24.743 --> 02:13:28.179
No. it's my pleasure. No money.

1273
02:13:28.280 --> 02:13:31.238
Take it as a gift.

1274
02:13:31.883 --> 02:13:36.486
If there is something I can do for you.
you come. we talk.

1275
02:13:53.338 --> 02:13:57.399
Signora Colombo. why
have you come to see me?

1276
02:13:59.511 --> 02:14:05.609
Your wife told me that
I should ask for your help.

1277
02:14:05.784 --> 02:14:08.309
She is in bad trouble.

1278
02:14:08.487 --> 02:14:12.389
Her neighbours complained
to the landlord about her dog.

1279
02:14:13.825 --> 02:14:16.555
He told her to get rid of the animal.

1280
02:14:16.795 --> 02:14:20.094
But her little boy loves that dog.

1281
02:14:20.332 --> 02:14:22.800
so she hid it.

1282
02:14:22.901 --> 02:14:25.369
When the landlord found out.

1283
02:14:25.470 --> 02:14:27.404
he got mad and told her to leave.

1284
02:14:27.506 --> 02:14:32.466
Now she can't stay
even if she gets rid of it.

1285
02:14:32.644 --> 02:14:34.703
I'm so ashamed!

1286
02:14:34.913 --> 02:14:41.011
He said he'd get the police to
throw us out on the street.

1287
02:14:42.120 --> 02:14:46.216
I'm sorry. but...

1288
02:14:46.358 --> 02:14:50.021
I could give you a couple
of dollars to help you move.

1289
02:14:50.128 --> 02:14:52.221
I can't move!

1290
02:14:52.697 --> 02:14:55.257
I want you to talk to him!

1291
02:14:55.434 --> 02:14:58.301
Tell him I want to stay here.

1292
02:15:05.944 --> 02:15:07.605
What is his name?

1293
02:15:07.779 --> 02:15:10.270
His name is Signor Roberto.

1294
02:15:10.415 --> 02:15:13.145
He lives on Fourth Street near here.

1295
02:15:13.585 --> 02:15:17.112
They break windows. dirty the floors...

1296
02:15:17.322 --> 02:15:19.517
A real pigsty?

1297
02:15:36.908 --> 02:15:39.706
My name is Vito Corleone.

1298
02:15:39.878 --> 02:15:43.109
Signora Colombo is a friend of my wife.

1299
02:15:43.281 --> 02:15:47.149
She says she is been
evicted for no good reason.

1300
02:15:47.252 --> 02:15:51.018
She is a poor widow and
has nobody to take care of her.

1301
02:15:51.223 --> 02:15:54.351
She has no relatives. no money.

1302
02:15:54.459 --> 02:15:55.958
All she has is this neighbourhood.

1303
02:15:56.027 --> 02:15:59.690
I've already rented the
place to another family.

1304
02:16:03.935 --> 02:16:07.132
I told her that I'd talk to you.

1305
02:16:07.305 --> 02:16:10.172
that you're a reasonable man.

1306
02:16:11.209 --> 02:16:15.111
She got rid of the animal
that caused all the trouble.

1307
02:16:15.213 --> 02:16:17.373
so let her stay.

1308
02:16:17.435 --> 02:16:19.997
Impossible.

1309
02:16:20.118 --> 02:16:23.281
Are you Sicilian?
No. I'm Calabrian.

1310
02:16:24.055 --> 02:16:27.582
Do me this favour. please.
as we're almost paesani.

1311
02:16:27.759 --> 02:16:30.160
I've already rented it!

1312
02:16:30.184 --> 02:16:32.284
 I'll look like an idiot.

1313
02:16:32.731 --> 02:16:34.560
Besides. the new tenants pay more rent.

1314
02:16:34.633 --> 02:16:37.227
How much more do they pay a month?

1315
02:16:37.435 --> 02:16:39.699
Five bucks.

1316
02:16:44.075 --> 02:16:46.539
Here is six months' increase in advance.

1317
02:16:46.811 --> 02:16:51.041
But don't tell her about it.
She is very proud.

1318
02:16:51.049 --> 02:16:53.945
Come and see me in six months again.

1319
02:16:55.520 --> 02:16:58.318
And the dog stays.
of course. Right?

1320
02:16:59.357 --> 02:17:00.822
The dog stays.

1321
02:17:00.892 --> 02:17:08.424
Do you think you can order me around?

1322
02:17:08.667 --> 02:17:14.172
Watch out. or I'll kick your
Sicilian ass right into the street!

1323
02:17:15.173 --> 02:17:20.770
Do me this favour. I won't forget it.

1324
02:17:20.946 --> 02:17:25.110
Ask your friends in the neighbourhood about me.

1325
02:17:25.283 --> 02:17:30.987
They'll tell you I know
how to return a favour.

1326
02:17:34.526 --> 02:17:36.554
What a character!

1327
02:17:43.535 --> 02:17:46.129
That landlord is here. Roberto.

1328
02:17:46.905 --> 02:17:49.601
who owns those ratholes.

1329
02:17:57.682 --> 02:18:01.140
He's been asking everyone in
the neighbourhood about you.

1330
02:18:07.726 --> 02:18:12.129
I hope I'm not disturbing you. Don Vito.

1331
02:18:12.364 --> 02:18:15.162
What can I do for you. Don Roberto?

1332
02:18:15.600 --> 02:18:19.400
What a misunderstanding! Holy Mary!

1333
02:18:19.838 --> 02:18:24.871
Signora Colombo can stay!
Of course she can stay!

1334
02:18:27.846 --> 02:18:33.482
I'm returning the money you gave me.

1335
02:18:33.918 --> 02:18:39.821
Un. due. three. four. five. six. tutt'!

1336
02:18:40.392 --> 02:18:45.830
Because. Don Vito. money isn't everything.

1337
02:18:53.805 --> 02:18:55.329
Can I sit down?

1338
02:18:58.410 --> 02:19:02.073
Your kindness to that widow
made me ashamed of myself.

1339
02:19:02.247 --> 02:19:05.774
The rent stays like before!

1340
02:19:13.658 --> 02:19:16.821
No. I'll lower it...

1341
02:19:19.631 --> 02:19:22.429
...five bucks. Okay?

1342
02:19:25.036 --> 02:19:27.129
No. ten bucks!

1343
02:19:31.342 --> 02:19:35.172
Some coffee?

1344
02:19:35.647 --> 02:19:41.085
I'm late for an appointment!

1345
02:19:41.186 --> 02:19:45.316
I can't. Ask me another time.

1346
02:19:45.423 --> 02:19:50.924
You'll have to excuse me for now.

1347
02:19:52.731 --> 02:19:55.136
I wish I could stay longer!

1348
02:20:01.139 --> 02:20:06.310
Just call me and I'll be here!

1349
02:20:16.421 --> 02:20:20.414
He won't be back. He'll
hide out in the Bronx.

1350
02:20:35.273 --> 02:20:37.841
Vito. what do you think?
God bless America.

1351
02:20:37.876 --> 02:20:39.901
We are gonna make a big business!

1352
02:20:47.385 --> 02:20:50.245
New York City.
Would you mind speaking up. please?

1353
02:20:50.789 --> 02:20:52.416
New York City.

1354
02:20:52.590 --> 02:20:56.048
Are you the son of Vito Corleone?
Yes. I am.

1355
02:20:56.394 --> 02:20:58.086
And where was he born?

1356
02:20:58.163 --> 02:20:59.824
Corleone. Sicily.

1357
02:20:59.931 --> 02:21:02.126
Did he at times use an alias

1358
02:21:02.233 --> 02:21:05.964
that was known in certain
circles as Godfather?

1359
02:21:06.805 --> 02:21:10.206
Godfather is a term that
was used by his friends.

1360
02:21:10.375 --> 02:21:13.235
One of affection. one of respect.

1361
02:21:13.611 --> 02:21:14.905
Mr Chairman.

1362
02:21:14.979 --> 02:21:17.773
I would like to verify the witness's statement.

1363
02:21:18.349 --> 02:21:23.116
For years now a growing number of my
constituents have been of italian descent.

1364
02:21:23.621 --> 02:21:25.646
And I've come to know them well.

1365
02:21:26.324 --> 02:21:30.556
They have honoured me with their
support and with their friendship.

1366
02:21:30.728 --> 02:21:32.093
Indeed I can proudly say

1367
02:21:32.197 --> 02:21:36.027
that some of my very best
friends are italian-Americans.

1368
02:21:37.101 --> 02:21:42.164
However. Mr Chairman. at this time very
unfortunately I have to leave these proceedings.

1369
02:21:42.273 --> 02:21:44.935
in order to preside over
a very important meeting

1370
02:21:45.076 --> 02:21:46.941
of my own committee.

1371
02:21:47.312 --> 02:21:50.340
But before I leave.
I do want to say this.

1372
02:21:50.682 --> 02:21:55.085
that these hearings on the
Mafia are in no way whatsoever

1373
02:21:55.186 --> 02:21:57.711
a slur upon the great italian people.

1374
02:21:57.822 --> 02:22:00.950
Because I can state from my
own knowledge and experience

1375
02:22:01.125 --> 02:22:06.188
that Italian-Americans are among
the most loyal. most law-abiding.

1376
02:22:06.364 --> 02:22:10.357
patriotic. hard-working
American citizens in this land.

1377
02:22:10.902 --> 02:22:15.839
It would be a shame. Mr Chairman.
if we allowed a few rotten apples

1378
02:22:15.974 --> 02:22:18.465
to give a bad name to the whole barrel.

1379
02:22:18.643 --> 02:22:21.237
Because from the time of the
great Christopher Columbus

1380
02:22:21.412 --> 02:22:23.972
up through the time of Enrico Fermi.

1381
02:22:24.082 --> 02:22:25.520
right up to the present day.

1382
02:22:25.659 --> 02:22:29.559
Italian-Americans have been pioneers
in building and defending our great nation.

1383
02:22:31.089 --> 02:22:32.784
They are the salt of the earth.

1384
02:22:32.957 --> 02:22:35.755
and they are one of the
backbones of this country.

1385
02:22:42.333 --> 02:22:45.266
I'm sure we all agree with
our esteemed colleague.

1386
02:22:46.104 --> 02:22:47.262
Now Mr Corleone.

1387
02:22:47.272 --> 02:22:50.070
you have been advised
as to your legal rights.

1388
02:22:50.608 --> 02:22:52.573
We have testimony from a witness.

1389
02:22:52.644 --> 02:22:53.904
a previous witness.

1390
02:22:53.912 --> 02:22:56.106
one Willi Cicci.

1391
02:22:57.115 --> 02:22:58.412
He stated that you are

1392
02:22:58.549 --> 02:23:01.250
head of the most powerful
Mafia family in this country.

1393
02:23:01.552 --> 02:23:03.750
Are you?
No. I'm not.

1394
02:23:03.955 --> 02:23:07.322
The witness has testified that
you are personally responsible

1395
02:23:07.492 --> 02:23:12.759
for the murder of a New York police
captain in 1947. and with him a man named

1396
02:23:12.864 --> 02:23:14.857
Virgil Sollozzo.

1397
02:23:15.066 --> 02:23:17.591
You deny this?
Yes. I do.

1398
02:23:17.702 --> 02:23:20.106
Is it true that in the year 1950

1399
02:23:20.140 --> 02:23:25.340
you devised the murder of the heads of
the so-called "Five Families" in New York.

1400
02:23:26.577 --> 02:23:30.069
to assume and consolidate your nefarious power?

1401
02:23:30.248 --> 02:23:32.341
That is a complete falsehood.

1402
02:23:32.517 --> 02:23:33.743
Mr Questadt.

1403
02:23:33.785 --> 02:23:38.381
Is it true you have a controlling interest
in three of the major hotels in Las Vegas?

1404
02:23:39.290 --> 02:23:40.516
No. it's not true.

1405
02:23:40.525 --> 02:23:43.050
I own some stock in some
of the hotels there.

1406
02:23:43.227 --> 02:23:44.524
but very little.

1407
02:23:47.332 --> 02:23:51.564
I also have stock in IBM and AT&T.

1408
02:23:51.565 --> 02:23:52.745
Mr. Corleone.

1409
02:23:52.770 --> 02:23:56.900
do you have any interests or
control over gambling and narcotics

1410
02:23:57.075 --> 02:24:00.106
in the state of New York?
No. I do not.

1411
02:24:00.411 --> 02:24:03.445
Senator. my client would like to read
a statement before this committee.

1412
02:24:03.469 --> 02:24:04.915
Mr Chairman.

1413
02:24:05.416 --> 02:24:07.611
Mr Chairman. I think this statement

1414
02:24:07.785 --> 02:24:09.878
is totally out of order at this time.

1415
02:24:09.988 --> 02:24:12.855
Sir. my client has answered
every questions

1416
02:24:13.024 --> 02:24:15.084
asked this committee with utmost sincerity

1417
02:24:15.167 --> 02:24:18.468
He hasn't taken the Fifth Amendment.
as it was his right to do.

1418
02:24:19.397 --> 02:24:22.091
So in all fairness I think the
statement should be heard!

1419
02:24:23.801 --> 02:24:26.834
No. I'm going to allow Mr
Corleone to read his statement.

1420
02:24:27.305 --> 02:24:29.168
I'll put it in the record.

1421
02:24:30.608 --> 02:24:33.202
In the hopes of clearing my family name.

1422
02:24:33.644 --> 02:24:35.974
and in the sincere desire to
give my children their fair share

1423
02:24:36.014 --> 02:24:37.743
of the American way of life

1424
02:24:37.915 --> 02:24:40.440
without a blemish on their
name and background.

1425
02:24:40.952 --> 02:24:45.885
I have appeared before this committee
and given it all the cooperation in my power.

1426
02:24:47.492 --> 02:24:49.628
I consider it a great dishonour
to me personally

1427
02:24:49.652 --> 02:24:52.152
to have to deny that I am a criminal.

1428
02:24:54.098 --> 02:24:56.794
I wish to have the following
noted for the record:

1429
02:24:57.568 --> 02:24:59.263
That I served my country faithfully

1430
02:24:59.437 --> 02:25:01.735
and honorably in World War Two

1431
02:25:01.906 --> 02:25:04.170
and was awarded the Navy Cross

1432
02:25:04.275 --> 02:25:06.675
for actions in defence of my country.

1433
02:25:07.745 --> 02:25:11.538
That I have never been arrested
or indicted for any crime whatsoever.

1434
02:25:12.083 --> 02:25:15.712
That no proof linking me
to any criminal conspiracy.

1435
02:25:16.320 --> 02:25:19.221
whether it is called Mafia or Cosa Nostra

1436
02:25:19.390 --> 02:25:23.224
or whatever other name you wish
to give has ever been made public.

1437
02:25:23.694 --> 02:25:26.595
I have not taken refuge
behind the Fifth Amendment.

1438
02:25:26.764 --> 02:25:28.464
although it was my right to do so.

1439
02:25:31.803 --> 02:25:33.896
I challenge this committee

1440
02:25:34.072 --> 02:25:37.041
to produce any witness
or evidence against me.

1441
02:25:37.575 --> 02:25:39.167
and if they do not.

1442
02:25:40.011 --> 02:25:42.104
I hope they will have the decency

1443
02:25:42.213 --> 02:25:45.273
to clear my name with the same publicity

1444
02:25:45.450 --> 02:25:47.645
with which they have now besmirched it.

1445
02:25:48.686 --> 02:25:51.414
I'm sure we're all quite
impressed. Mr. Corleone.

1446
02:25:51.489 --> 02:25:53.684
Particularly with your
love for our country.

1447
02:25:54.192 --> 02:25:56.922
We'll stand in recess until
10 a.m. Monday morning.

1448
02:25:57.095 --> 02:25:59.356
at which time we will produce a witness

1449
02:25:59.430 --> 02:26:02.021
who'll corroborate the charges
that were made against you today.

1450
02:26:02.066 --> 02:26:03.690
At which time. Mr. Corleone.

1451
02:26:03.701 --> 02:26:07.000
you may very well be subject
to indictment for perjury.

1452
02:26:07.105 --> 02:26:10.233
I remind you that you're still
under subpoena. Mr. Corleone.

1453
02:26:10.257 --> 02:26:12.057
This court is adjourned.

1454
02:26:15.613 --> 02:26:18.275
Ten to one shot. you said.

1455
02:26:18.299 --> 02:26:20.117
Ten to one shot.

1456
02:26:20.118 --> 02:26:23.281
he would take the Fifth. and I lose.

1457
02:26:23.454 --> 02:26:25.445
You sound like my bookie.

1458
02:26:25.623 --> 02:26:27.650
I owe that monkey my life.

1459
02:26:29.227 --> 02:26:31.022
Well. just get a good night's sleep.

1460
02:26:31.095 --> 02:26:32.685
Yeah. a good nights sleep.

1461
02:26:32.697 --> 02:26:34.528
You've got a big day tomorrow.

1462
02:26:34.999 --> 02:26:38.696
I got you a new suit.
a new shirt. new tie.

1463
02:26:39.403 --> 02:26:41.871
I'm gonna shave you myself in the morning.

1464
02:26:42.807 --> 02:26:44.704
You're gonna look
respectable for 50 million

1465
02:26:44.842 --> 02:26:46.639
of your fellow Americans.

1466
02:26:46.911 --> 02:26:51.842
Tomorrow! My life won't be
worth a nickel after tomorrow.

1467
02:26:53.184 --> 02:26:56.084
Come on! I saw this 19 times.

1468
02:26:57.989 --> 02:27:00.150
You've got a great home here. Frankie.

1469
02:27:00.625 --> 02:27:02.650
for the rest of your life.
Nobody gets near you.

1470
02:27:02.827 --> 02:27:04.392
you're not going anywhere.

1471
02:27:04.629 --> 02:27:07.196
That's great. That's beautiful.

1472
02:27:08.032 --> 02:27:09.897
Some deal I made.

1473
02:27:10.168 --> 02:27:12.693
You'll live like a king. You'll be a hero.

1474
02:27:12.970 --> 02:27:15.705
You'll live better in here than
most people on the outside.

1475
02:27:16.073 --> 02:27:17.438
Some deal!

1476
02:27:20.288 --> 02:27:21.688
Alive.

1477
02:27:22.313 --> 02:27:24.311
Pentangeli is alive.

1478
02:27:26.684 --> 02:27:28.313
How did they get their hands on him?

1479
02:27:28.586 --> 02:27:31.454
Roth. He engineered it. Michael.

1480
02:27:32.723 --> 02:27:35.123
Frankie went to make a
deal with the Rosato brothers

1481
02:27:35.293 --> 02:27:37.124
and they tried to kill him.

1482
02:27:37.295 --> 02:27:39.160
He thought you double-crossed him.

1483
02:27:40.731 --> 02:27:43.456
Our people with the  New York detectives
said he was half dead. scared stiff.

1484
02:27:43.501 --> 02:27:46.299
and calling out loud that
you had turned on him.

1485
02:27:46.904 --> 02:27:48.337
They already had him on possession.

1486
02:27:48.506 --> 02:27:50.934
bookmaking. murder one and a lot more.

1487
02:27:53.044 --> 02:27:55.340
The FBI has him airtight.

1488
02:27:55.980 --> 02:27:58.276
He is on an army base. 24 hour guards.

1489
02:27:58.816 --> 02:28:00.883
No way we can get to him.

1490
02:28:01.852 --> 02:28:03.779
You've opened yourself
to five counts of perjury.

1491
02:28:06.257 --> 02:28:09.124
What about Fredo? What does he know?

1492
02:28:09.293 --> 02:28:10.760
He says he doesn't know anything.

1493
02:28:10.928 --> 02:28:12.361
and I believe him.

1494
02:28:13.197 --> 02:28:14.593
Roth. well he...

1495
02:28:15.242 --> 02:28:16.942
played this one beautifully.

1496
02:28:25.009 --> 02:28:26.636
I want to talk to Fredo.

1497
02:29:06.851 --> 02:29:08.917
I haven't got a lot to say. Mike.

1498
02:29:11.155 --> 02:29:12.684
We have time.

1499
02:29:13.824 --> 02:29:16.059
I was kept pretty much in the dark.

1500
02:29:18.296 --> 02:29:20.161
I didn't know all that much.

1501
02:29:21.365 --> 02:29:22.889
What about now?

1502
02:29:24.201 --> 02:29:26.229
Is there anything you
can help me out with?

1503
02:29:26.453 --> 02:29:28.453
Anything you can tell me now?

1504
02:29:31.075 --> 02:29:33.605
They've got Pentangeli.
that's all I can tell you.

1505
02:29:48.326 --> 02:29:51.027
I didn't know it was gonna be a hit. Mike.

1506
02:29:52.129 --> 02:29:54.730
I swear to God I didn't know
it was gonna be a hit.

1507
02:29:57.335 --> 02:29:59.633
Johnny Ola bumped into me

1508
02:29:59.870 --> 02:30:01.735
in Beverly Hills.

1509
02:30:03.541 --> 02:30:05.608
He said that he wanted to talk.

1510
02:30:08.179 --> 02:30:12.951
He said that you and Roth
were in on a big deal together.

1511
02:30:16.821 --> 02:30:21.019
And that there was something in
it for me if I could help him out.

1512
02:30:21.158 --> 02:30:25.060
He said that you were being
tough on the negotiations.

1513
02:30:25.262 --> 02:30:27.253
but if they could get a little help

1514
02:30:27.531 --> 02:30:29.829
and close the deal fast.

1515
02:30:31.168 --> 02:30:34.228
it would be good for the family.

1516
02:30:35.239 --> 02:30:37.198
And you believed that story?

1517
02:30:38.209 --> 02:30:39.736
You believed that?

1518
02:30:40.010 --> 02:30:42.344
He said there was something in it for me.

1519
02:30:42.580 --> 02:30:46.016
on my own!
I've always taken care of you. Fredo.

1520
02:30:46.384 --> 02:30:48.318
Taken care of me?!

1521
02:30:49.453 --> 02:30:52.718
You're my kid brother! You take care of me?

1522
02:30:53.257 --> 02:30:54.918
Did you ever think about that?

1523
02:30:55.092 --> 02:30:57.993
Did you ever once think about that?

1524
02:30:58.496 --> 02:30:59.861
"Send Fredo off to do this.

1525
02:30:59.964 --> 02:31:02.159
send Fredo off to do that!"

1526
02:31:03.267 --> 02:31:07.704
"Let Fredo take care of some Mickey
Mouse nightclub somewhere."

1527
02:31:07.872 --> 02:31:10.800
"Let Fredo pick somebody
up at the airport!"

1528
02:31:11.142 --> 02:31:12.541
I'm your older brother. Mike.

1529
02:31:12.676 --> 02:31:14.303
and I was stepped over!

1530
02:31:14.412 --> 02:31:17.609
That's the way Pop wanted it.
It ain't the way I wanted it!

1531
02:31:18.816 --> 02:31:21.512
I can handle things. I'm smart!

1532
02:31:21.752 --> 02:31:24.721
Not like everybody says. Like dumb.

1533
02:31:24.822 --> 02:31:27.689
I'm smart and I want respect!

1534
02:31:35.699 --> 02:31:39.396
Is there anything you can tell
me about this investigation?

1535
02:31:39.503 --> 02:31:40.895
Anything more?

1536
02:31:48.779 --> 02:31:51.046
The senate lawyer. Questadt...

1537
02:31:52.894 --> 02:31:54.594
He belongs to Roth.

1538
02:32:04.628 --> 02:32:05.890
Fredo.

1539
02:32:08.699 --> 02:32:10.658
you're nothing to me now.

1540
02:32:13.270 --> 02:32:16.301
You are not a brother.
you are not a friend.

1541
02:32:17.374 --> 02:32:19.670
I don't want to know you.
or what you do.

1542
02:32:21.745 --> 02:32:23.713
I don't want to see you at the hotels.

1543
02:32:24.715 --> 02:32:26.783
I don't want you near my house.

1544
02:32:29.220 --> 02:32:30.787
When you see our mother.

1545
02:32:30.811 --> 02:32:33.611
I want to know a day in
advance. so I won't be there.

1546
02:32:35.426 --> 02:32:36.989
You understand?

1547
02:32:47.037 --> 02:32:48.466
Mikey.

1548
02:32:55.379 --> 02:32:58.809
I don't want anything to happen
to him while my mother is alive.

1549
02:33:49.233 --> 02:33:51.399
More people than
a ballgame in here.

1550
02:33:52.603 --> 02:33:54.698
Hey. that is Willi Cicci!

1551
02:33:54.722 --> 02:33:56.522
Frankie Five-Angels.

1552
02:34:16.527 --> 02:34:18.695
This committee will come to order!

1553
02:34:21.632 --> 02:34:22.963
State your name. please.

1554
02:34:23.133 --> 02:34:24.498
Frank Pentangeli.

1555
02:34:24.668 --> 02:34:25.826
And where were you born?

1556
02:34:25.836 --> 02:34:28.270
Par Panico. it is outside of Palermo.

1557
02:34:28.405 --> 02:34:29.995
And where do you live now?

1558
02:34:30.674 --> 02:34:35.168
I live in an army barracks
with the FBI guys.

1559
02:34:36.847 --> 02:34:39.307
We have here finally a witness

1560
02:34:39.516 --> 02:34:42.610
that will further testify to Michael Corleone's

1561
02:34:42.720 --> 02:34:44.688
rule over a criminal empire that

1562
02:34:44.855 --> 02:34:46.722
controls all the gambling in this country

1563
02:34:46.821 --> 02:34:48.299
and perhaps other countries.

1564
02:34:48.325 --> 02:34:50.225
This witness has had no buffer

1565
02:34:50.361 --> 02:34:52.652
between himself and Michael Corleone.

1566
02:34:53.097 --> 02:34:54.223
He can corroborate

1567
02:34:54.365 --> 02:34:57.330
our charges on enough
counts for this committee

1568
02:34:57.368 --> 02:35:01.036
to recommend a charge of
perjury against Michael Corleone.

1569
02:35:01.372 --> 02:35:03.470
Senator.
Thank you. Chairman.

1570
02:35:04.675 --> 02:35:06.440
Mr Pentangeli...

1571
02:35:07.578 --> 02:35:09.312
Mr Pentangeli.

1572
02:35:10.014 --> 02:35:12.744
Were you a member of the Corleone family?

1573
02:35:13.250 --> 02:35:18.247
Did you serve under Caporegime.
Peter Clemenza.

1574
02:35:18.455 --> 02:35:22.658
under Vito Corleone.
also known as the Godfather?

1575
02:35:28.799 --> 02:35:31.568
I never know no godfather.

1576
02:35:33.971 --> 02:35:36.331
I have my own family. senator.

1577
02:35:39.476 --> 02:35:41.273
Mr Pentangeli. you...

1578
02:35:41.945 --> 02:35:45.970
You are contradicting a sworn statement
that you previously made to me and signed.

1579
02:35:46.784 --> 02:35:48.445
I ask you again. sir.

1580
02:35:48.619 --> 02:35:50.246
here and now under oath.

1581
02:35:50.354 --> 02:35:56.223
were you at any time a member of a crime
organisation headed by Michael Corleone?

1582
02:35:56.727 --> 02:35:58.490
I don't know nothing about that!

1583
02:36:02.566 --> 02:36:06.263
I was in the olive oil business with his father.

1584
02:36:06.670 --> 02:36:09.764
but that was a long
time ago.That's all.

1585
02:36:10.507 --> 02:36:13.074
We have a sworn affidavit.

1586
02:36:13.677 --> 02:36:16.646
We have it. Your sworn affidavit

1587
02:36:16.780 --> 02:36:19.806
that you murdered on the
orders of Michael Corleone.

1588
02:36:19.917 --> 02:36:21.782
Do you deny this confession.

1589
02:36:21.885 --> 02:36:24.681
and do you realise what will
happen as a result of your denial?

1590
02:36:24.688 --> 02:36:27.357
Look the FBI guys promised me a deal.

1591
02:36:27.825 --> 02:36:31.625
So I made up a lot of stuff
about Michael Corleone.

1592
02:36:31.729 --> 02:36:33.492
'cause that's what they wanted.

1593
02:36:33.764 --> 02:36:35.755
But it was all lies.

1594
02:36:36.133 --> 02:36:38.028
Everything!

1595
02:36:38.602 --> 02:36:42.466
They kept saying "Michael Corleone did this"

1596
02:36:43.440 --> 02:36:45.904
and "Michael Corleone did that".

1597
02:36:47.277 --> 02:36:51.338
So I said. "Yeah. sure. Why not?"

1598
02:36:51.615 --> 02:36:52.946
Mr Corleone.

1599
02:36:53.117 --> 02:36:55.685
would you kindly identify
for the committee

1600
02:36:55.753 --> 02:36:57.653
the gentleman sitting to your left?

1601
02:36:57.821 --> 02:36:59.220
I can answer that.

1602
02:37:00.157 --> 02:37:02.990
His name is Vincenzo Pentangeli.

1603
02:37:03.427 --> 02:37:05.418
Is he related to the witness?

1604
02:37:06.096 --> 02:37:07.825
He is. I believe. his brother.

1605
02:37:08.332 --> 02:37:10.425
Will he come forward and be sworn. sir?

1606
02:37:10.768 --> 02:37:12.998
Sir. this man does not understand English.

1607
02:37:13.170 --> 02:37:14.294
He came at his own expense

1608
02:37:14.304 --> 02:37:16.570
to aid his brother
in his time of trouble.

1609
02:37:16.840 --> 02:37:18.436
He is not under subpoena.

1610
02:37:18.445 --> 02:37:20.694
And his reputation in his
own country is impeccable.

1611
02:37:20.744 --> 02:37:22.539
Are you saying that he knows
nothing about these matters?

1612
02:37:22.613 --> 02:37:24.410
To my knowledge. nothing.

1613
02:37:24.581 --> 02:37:27.175
I'm gonna find out what
the hell happened here!

1614
02:37:27.351 --> 02:37:29.612
Alright. this committee is now adjourned.

1615
02:37:29.686 --> 02:37:31.878
The witness is excused.
Senator!

1616
02:37:32.723 --> 02:37:33.812
Senator!

1617
02:37:33.891 --> 02:37:36.291
This committee owes an apology!

1618
02:37:36.894 --> 02:37:40.755
This committee owes an
apology. Apology. Senator!

1619
02:38:08.458 --> 02:38:12.261
Michael. excuse me.
Hello. darling.

1620
02:38:13.030 --> 02:38:15.498
The children are outside.
We are going.

1621
02:38:17.768 --> 02:38:20.530
What do you mean going?
We're all gonna leave tomorrow.

1622
02:38:21.605 --> 02:38:22.870
Rocco?

1623
02:38:24.344 --> 02:38:26.144
I'll be in my room. Mike.

1624
02:38:30.080 --> 02:38:32.480
Michael. I'm not going back to Nevada.

1625
02:38:33.150 --> 02:38:35.751
I brought the children
to say goodbye to you.

1626
02:38:39.756 --> 02:38:42.416
I want you to know
I'm very happy for you.

1627
02:38:42.492 --> 02:38:45.017
I suppose I always knew
you were too smart

1628
02:38:45.195 --> 02:38:47.290
to let any of them ever beat you.

1629
02:38:48.465 --> 02:38:52.768
Why don't you sit down?
No. I'm not going to stay long. I can't.

1630
02:38:53.136 --> 02:38:55.427
There are some things I'd
like to talk to you about.

1631
02:38:57.441 --> 02:38:59.534
Things that have been on my mind.

1632
02:39:00.777 --> 02:39:02.310
changes I want to make.

1633
02:39:02.379 --> 02:39:05.248
I think it's too late for changes. Michael.

1634
02:39:06.516 --> 02:39:08.914
I promised myself  I wasn't
going to say anything and now...

1635
02:39:08.986 --> 02:39:11.250
What do you mean. "too late"?

1636
02:39:16.593 --> 02:39:19.321
What really happened
with Pentangeli. Michael?

1637
02:39:25.235 --> 02:39:27.135
His brother came and helped him.

1638
02:39:27.471 --> 02:39:29.302
I didn't even know he had a brother.

1639
02:39:30.440 --> 02:39:31.964
Where is he now?

1640
02:39:33.577 --> 02:39:36.244
He is on a plane back to Sicily.

1641
02:39:37.047 --> 02:39:39.413
All he had to do was show his face.

1642
02:39:41.218 --> 02:39:43.316
It was between the brothers. Kay.

1643
02:39:44.087 --> 02:39:45.946
I had nothing to do with it.

1644
02:39:53.897 --> 02:39:56.923
I don't want you going.
Not you. not the kids. No.

1645
02:39:57.415 --> 02:40:00.851
You're my wife and they are children.

1646
02:40:00.896 --> 02:40:02.725
I love you and won't
allow it. That's it.

1647
02:40:03.540 --> 02:40:07.342
Michael. you say you love me. and then
you talk about allowing me to leave!

1648
02:40:07.544 --> 02:40:10.538
There are things that have been going
on for years between men and women

1649
02:40:10.622 --> 02:40:13.811
that will not change. That's it.
Michael. you've become blind!

1650
02:40:13.817 --> 02:40:16.275
Blind to what?
Look what's happened to us. Mike.

1651
02:40:16.276 --> 02:40:18.295
My God. look what's happened
to our son. Michael.

1652
02:40:18.822 --> 02:40:20.549
Nothing's happened to him.
Don't tell me nothing's...

1653
02:40:20.557 --> 02:40:22.249
Anthony is fine!
Anthony is not fine!

1654
02:40:22.326 --> 02:40:24.057
I don't want to hear about it.
You will.

1655
02:40:24.081 --> 02:40:26.361
I don't wanna hear about it!
Anthony's friends...

1656
02:40:26.362 --> 02:40:28.572
...are your buttonmen!
I don't want to hear about it!

1657
02:40:29.900 --> 02:40:31.390
Over!

1658
02:40:44.281 --> 02:40:46.615
At this moment I feel
no love for you at all.

1659
02:40:48.952 --> 02:40:51.653
I never thought that would ever happen.

1660
02:40:52.456 --> 02:40:54.122
but it has.

1661
02:41:08.171 --> 02:41:09.502
Kay...

1662
02:41:13.410 --> 02:41:15.137
We're gonna leave tomorrow.

1663
02:41:15.979 --> 02:41:18.873
Kay. why don't you take
the kids back to their room?

1664
02:41:19.182 --> 02:41:21.309
Michael. you haven't heard me.

1665
02:41:21.418 --> 02:41:24.085
Kay. what do you want from me?

1666
02:41:25.455 --> 02:41:27.621
Do you expect me to let you go?

1667
02:41:27.924 --> 02:41:31.418
Do you expect me to let you
take my children from me?

1668
02:41:32.529 --> 02:41:33.857
Don't you know me?

1669
02:41:33.864 --> 02:41:36.698
Don't you know that is an impossibility
that that could never happen.?

1670
02:41:38.201 --> 02:41:41.565
That I'd use all my power to keep
something like that from happening?

1671
02:41:42.806 --> 02:41:44.638
Don't you know that?

1672
02:41:46.910 --> 02:41:48.209
Kay...

1673
02:41:51.982 --> 02:41:53.613
in time.

1674
02:41:54.851 --> 02:41:56.685
you'll feel differently.

1675
02:41:57.988 --> 02:42:00.248
You'll be glad I stopped you now.

1676
02:42:02.759 --> 02:42:04.351
I know that.

1677
02:42:06.763 --> 02:42:09.732
I know you blame me for losing the baby.

1678
02:42:11.902 --> 02:42:15.966
Yes. I know what that meant to you.

1679
02:42:19.276 --> 02:42:21.244
I'll make it up to you. Kay.

1680
02:42:22.112 --> 02:42:24.740
I swear I'll make it up to you. I'll...

1681
02:42:26.283 --> 02:42:27.917
I'm gonna change.

1682
02:42:29.553 --> 02:42:31.182
I'll change.

1683
02:42:31.455 --> 02:42:34.716
I've learned that I have
the strength to change.

1684
02:42:36.026 --> 02:42:38.354
Then you'll forget about
this miscarriage...

1685
02:42:39.863 --> 02:42:41.888
...and we'll have another child.

1686
02:42:42.065 --> 02:42:43.555
And we'll go on.

1687
02:42:43.767 --> 02:42:46.066
you and I. We'll go on.

1688
02:42:48.672 --> 02:42:50.599
Oh. Michael!

1689
02:42:51.374 --> 02:42:53.272
Michael. you are blind.

1690
02:42:55.378 --> 02:42:57.311
It wasn't a miscarriage.

1691
02:42:59.859 --> 02:43:01.659
It was an abortion.

1692
02:43:03.286 --> 02:43:09.191
An abortion. Michael. Just like
our marriage is an abortion.

1693
02:43:09.359 --> 02:43:13.193
Something that's unholy and evil!

1694
02:43:14.297 --> 02:43:17.198
I didn't want your son. Michael!

1695
02:43:17.734 --> 02:43:21.668
I wouldn't bring another one
of your sons into this world!

1696
02:43:23.340 --> 02:43:25.374
It was an abortion. Michael.

1697
02:43:25.909 --> 02:43:28.878
It was a son. a son
and I had it killed

1698
02:43:29.045 --> 02:43:31.571
because this must all end!

1699
02:43:33.116 --> 02:43:35.510
I know now that it is over.

1700
02:43:35.886 --> 02:43:37.711
I knew it then.

1701
02:43:38.588 --> 02:43:40.920
There would be no way. Michael.

1702
02:43:41.091 --> 02:43:44.060
no way you could ever forgive me.

1703
02:43:44.194 --> 02:43:49.159
Not with this Sicilian thing that's
been going on for 2.000 years...

1704
02:43:49.183 --> 02:43:50.583
Stop it!

1705
02:43:56.606 --> 02:43:59.871
You won't take my children.
I will.

1706
02:44:00.043 --> 02:44:04.103
You won't take my children!
They're my children too.

1707
02:45:34.057 --> 02:45:37.084
Fredo. give this to Grandmother.

1708
02:45:47.063 --> 02:45:49.263
Sonny. what you doing?
Don't make a fight.

1709
02:47:54.978 --> 02:47:56.570
Don Ciccio. it's Tommasino.

1710
02:47:56.679 --> 02:48:00.638
Allow me the honour of introducing someone.

1711
02:48:00.817 --> 02:48:03.377
My partner in America. in New York.

1712
02:48:03.686 --> 02:48:07.520
His name is Vito Corleone.

1713
02:48:07.624 --> 02:48:10.923
We're going to send him olive oil

1714
02:48:11.094 --> 02:48:17.260
from here to his company in America.

1715
02:48:17.434 --> 02:48:20.870
A big olive oil importer. Don Ciccio.

1716
02:48:29.412 --> 02:48:33.314
We would like your blessing

1717
02:48:33.516 --> 02:48:36.485
and your permission to start work.

1718
02:48:37.120 --> 02:48:40.886
Where is this young man from New York?

1719
02:48:43.193 --> 02:48:47.186
Have him come closer.

1720
02:48:47.363 --> 02:48:50.992
I can't see him very good.

1721
02:48:57.440 --> 02:48:59.135
My respects. Don Ciccio.

1722
02:48:59.309 --> 02:49:00.640
Give me your blessing.

1723
02:49:03.480 --> 02:49:05.072
Bless you!

1724
02:49:07.484 --> 02:49:09.315
What's your name?

1725
02:49:14.190 --> 02:49:17.648
You took the name of this town!

1726
02:49:17.827 --> 02:49:19.920
And what's your father's name?

1727
02:49:20.096 --> 02:49:23.998
His name was Antonio Andolini.

1728
02:49:24.167 --> 02:49:29.002
Louder. I don't hear very good.

1729
02:49:30.874 --> 02:49:34.275
My father's name was Antonio Andolini

1730
02:49:34.444 --> 02:49:37.311
and this is for you!

1731
02:50:58.995 --> 02:51:00.995
Michael. say goodbye.

1732
02:52:04.627 --> 02:52:05.992
Hi. Al.

1733
02:52:17.206 --> 02:52:20.242
Tom. can I speak with
you for a second. Tom?

1734
02:52:29.085 --> 02:52:30.450
Tom. where is Mike?

1735
02:52:31.954 --> 02:52:33.751
Waiting for you to leave.

1736
02:52:36.693 --> 02:52:38.220
Can I talk with him?

1737
02:52:38.828 --> 02:52:40.662
Sorry. Fredo. No chance.

1738
02:52:41.631 --> 02:52:44.689
Can I see him?
He is in the boathouse.

1739
02:52:58.247 --> 02:53:00.274
Michael. it is Connie.

1740
02:53:21.871 --> 02:53:23.304
Michael...

1741
02:53:26.375 --> 02:53:29.143
I'd like to stay close to
home now. if it is all right.

1742
02:53:38.454 --> 02:53:39.819
Is Kay coming?

1743
02:53:43.459 --> 02:53:44.690
No.

1744
02:53:52.535 --> 02:53:55.233
Michael. Fredo is in the house with Mama.

1745
02:53:55.838 --> 02:53:59.037
He asked for you and Tom
said you wouldn't see him.

1746
02:54:03.412 --> 02:54:04.877
That's right.

1747
02:54:08.151 --> 02:54:11.450
Kids. why don't you go outside for a while?

1748
02:54:15.224 --> 02:54:17.659
Mike. please. I want to talk to you.

1749
02:54:28.938 --> 02:54:31.800
Michael. I hated you for so many years.

1750
02:54:33.609 --> 02:54:35.740
I think I did things to myself.

1751
02:54:35.964 --> 02:54:37.445
to hurt myself.

1752
02:54:37.446 --> 02:54:39.179
so that you'd know...

1753
02:54:41.827 --> 02:54:43.527
that I could hurt you.

1754
02:54:50.359 --> 02:54:54.796
You were just being strong for
all of us. the way Papa was.

1755
02:54:55.231 --> 02:54:56.894
And I forgive you.

1756
02:55:01.604 --> 02:55:03.638
Can't you forgive Fredo?

1757
02:55:04.707 --> 02:55:06.666
He is so sweet.

1758
02:55:06.943 --> 02:55:09.039
and helpless without you.

1759
02:55:15.818 --> 02:55:17.251
You need me. Michael.

1760
02:55:17.386 --> 02:55:20.184
I want to take care of you now.

1761
02:55:29.432 --> 02:55:30.956
Connie...

1762
02:57:14.737 --> 02:57:16.170
Tom. sit down.

1763
02:57:27.616 --> 02:57:31.118
Our friend and business partner.
Hyman Roth. is in the news.

1764
02:57:32.621 --> 02:57:34.111
Did you hear about it?

1765
02:57:34.991 --> 02:57:36.752
I hear that he is in Israel.

1766
02:57:37.960 --> 02:57:39.291
The High Court in Israel

1767
02:57:39.462 --> 02:57:42.622
turned down his request to
live there as a return Jew.

1768
02:57:42.698 --> 02:57:46.156
His passport's been invalidated.
except for return to the United States.

1769
02:57:46.335 --> 02:57:48.833
He landed in Buenos Aires yesterday.

1770
02:57:49.305 --> 02:57:52.571
He offered a gift of a million dollars
if they'd let him live there.

1771
02:57:54.276 --> 02:57:55.976
They turned him down.

1772
02:57:56.479 --> 02:57:58.171
He is going to try Panama.

1773
02:57:58.347 --> 02:57:59.837
Panama won't take him.

1774
02:58:00.616 --> 02:58:02.982
Not for a million. not for ten million.

1775
02:58:03.352 --> 02:58:07.317
His medical condition is reported as terminal.
He is only to live another six months anyway.

1776
02:58:08.290 --> 02:58:11.316
He's been dying of the same
heart attack for tweny years.

1777
02:58:11.494 --> 02:58:13.189
That plane goes to Miami.

1778
02:58:13.295 --> 02:58:15.786
That's right. That's where I want it met.

1779
02:58:16.732 --> 02:58:18.290
Mike. that is impossible.

1780
02:58:18.467 --> 02:58:20.501
They'll turn him over directly
to the internal Revenue.

1781
02:58:20.569 --> 02:58:22.261
Customs and half the FBI.

1782
02:58:22.338 --> 02:58:23.705
It's not impossible.

1783
02:58:24.640 --> 02:58:25.864
Nothing is impossible.

1784
02:58:25.888 --> 02:58:28.975
I'd be like trying to kill the president.
There is no way we can get to him!

1785
02:58:29.211 --> 02:58:31.272
Tom. you know you surprise me.

1786
02:58:34.550 --> 02:58:36.677
If anything in this life is certain.

1787
02:58:38.120 --> 02:58:40.418
If history has taught us anything.

1788
02:58:41.524 --> 02:58:43.424
it is that you can kill anyone.

1789
02:58:49.398 --> 02:58:50.660
Rocco?

1790
02:58:51.434 --> 02:58:54.160
Difficuit. Not impossible.

1791
02:58:54.737 --> 02:58:56.032
Good.

1792
02:58:59.008 --> 02:59:02.244
Why did you ask me if something
was wrong when I came in?

1793
02:59:06.348 --> 02:59:08.575
I thought you were
going to tell me that

1794
02:59:09.919 --> 02:59:11.819
you're moving your family to Vegas...

1795
02:59:13.656 --> 02:59:17.852
...and that you'd been offered the Vice
Presidency of the House and hotels there.

1796
02:59:19.395 --> 02:59:21.292
I thought you were going to tell me that.
I turned them down.

1797
02:59:21.330 --> 02:59:23.928
Do I have to tell you about
every offer that I turn down?

1798
02:59:28.571 --> 02:59:30.967
Let's do business.
All right.

1799
02:59:33.042 --> 02:59:35.704
Just consider this. Michael.
That's all. Just consider it.

1800
02:59:37.279 --> 02:59:39.540
Now Roth and the Rosatos are on the run.

1801
02:59:39.615 --> 02:59:42.306
Are they worth it. are they strong enough?

1802
02:59:42.585 --> 02:59:44.077
Is it worth it?

1803
02:59:44.954 --> 02:59:47.648
I mean you've won. You
wanna wipe everybody out?

1804
02:59:47.656 --> 02:59:50.648
I don't feel I have to wipe
everybody out. Tom.

1805
02:59:51.160 --> 02:59:53.595
Just my enemies. that's all.

1806
03:00:00.503 --> 03:00:03.802
You gonna come along with me in
these things I have to do or what?

1807
03:00:05.207 --> 03:00:06.435
Because if not.

1808
03:00:06.509 --> 03:00:09.137
you can take your wife. your family

1809
03:00:09.311 --> 03:00:10.778
and your mistress.

1810
03:00:11.180 --> 03:00:13.045
and move them all to Las Vegas.

1811
03:00:17.286 --> 03:00:19.015
Why do you hurt me. Michael?

1812
03:00:19.188 --> 03:00:21.780
I've always been loyal to you.
I mean what is this?

1813
03:00:27.229 --> 03:00:29.254
So. you're staying?

1814
03:00:30.633 --> 03:00:32.730
Yes. I'm staying.

1815
03:00:35.971 --> 03:00:38.196
Now what is it that you want me to do?

1816
03:00:38.340 --> 03:00:39.673
Hey. Anthony...

1817
03:00:40.543 --> 03:00:42.577
How would you like it if I...

1818
03:00:42.578 --> 03:00:45.206
...if I taught you how to
catch the really big fish?

1819
03:00:45.314 --> 03:00:47.778
Would you like that?
Okay.

1820
03:00:48.284 --> 03:00:50.149
You know. when I was your age.

1821
03:00:51.153 --> 03:00:54.014
I went out to fishing with all my brothers

1822
03:00:54.823 --> 03:00:57.820
and my father. Everybody.

1823
03:00:59.328 --> 03:01:02.024
I was the only one that caught a fish.

1824
03:01:02.846 --> 03:01:05.104
Nobody else could catch
one ecept me.

1825
03:01:06.202 --> 03:01:07.801
Do you know how I did it?

1826
03:01:09.572 --> 03:01:11.199
Every time I put the line in the water

1827
03:01:11.373 --> 03:01:12.863
I said a Hail Mary

1828
03:01:13.375 --> 03:01:15.843
and every time I said a
Hail Mary. I caught a fish.

1829
03:01:19.515 --> 03:01:20.777
Do you believe that?

1830
03:01:21.016 --> 03:01:23.476
It is true. That's the secret.

1831
03:01:25.721 --> 03:01:27.584
You wanna try it when
we go out on the lake?

1832
03:01:27.590 --> 03:01:28.756
Okay.

1833
03:01:30.711 --> 03:01:32.171
What else you got?

1834
03:01:59.588 --> 03:02:01.853
Everything will be okay.
Frankie. Don't worry!

1835
03:02:01.857 --> 03:02:03.254
Did my brother go back?

1836
03:02:03.292 --> 03:02:05.119
Yeah. don't worry.

1837
03:02:05.928 --> 03:02:08.524
He is ten times tougher
than me. my brother.

1838
03:02:09.031 --> 03:02:10.728
He is old-fashioned.

1839
03:02:12.167 --> 03:02:15.064
He didn't want to go out to dinner.
He just wanted to go straight home.

1840
03:02:15.404 --> 03:02:16.598
That's my brother!

1841
03:02:16.705 --> 03:02:20.402
Listen. nothing could get him out.
get him away from that two-mule town.

1842
03:02:20.576 --> 03:02:23.804
He could've been big here.
He could've had his own family.

1843
03:02:29.818 --> 03:02:31.055
Tom...

1844
03:02:32.079 --> 03:02:33.679
what do I do now?

1845
03:02:35.691 --> 03:02:36.956
Frankie...

1846
03:02:42.231 --> 03:02:45.758
You were always interested
in politics and history.

1847
03:02:47.903 --> 03:02:50.633
I remember you talking
about Hitler back in '33.

1848
03:02:51.307 --> 03:02:54.799
Yeah. I still read a lot.
I get good stuff in there.

1849
03:02:57.579 --> 03:02:59.945
You were around the old-timers.

1850
03:03:00.249 --> 03:03:03.182
who dreamt of how the
family should be organized.

1851
03:03:03.218 --> 03:03:05.149
How they based them on
the old Roman legions. and

1852
03:03:05.154 --> 03:03:08.354
called them "regimes".
"capos" and "soldiers".

1853
03:03:10.092 --> 03:03:11.450
And it worked.

1854
03:03:12.127 --> 03:03:14.291
Yeah. it worked.

1855
03:03:14.897 --> 03:03:17.798
Those were the great old days. you know.

1856
03:03:18.500 --> 03:03:21.196
We was like the Roman Empire.

1857
03:03:21.637 --> 03:03:25.368
The Corleone family was
like the Roman Empire.

1858
03:03:27.863 --> 03:03:29.063
Yeah...

1859
03:03:29.845 --> 03:03:31.540
...it was once.

1860
03:03:36.452 --> 03:03:37.717
Frankie...

1861
03:03:48.697 --> 03:03:51.465
When a plot against the Emperor failed.

1862
03:03:53.502 --> 03:03:56.300
the plotters were always given a chance

1863
03:03:58.807 --> 03:04:01.904
to let their families keep
their fortunes. Right?

1864
03:04:02.678 --> 03:04:04.578
Yeah. but only the rich guys. Tom.

1865
03:04:04.713 --> 03:04:06.908
The little guys. they got knocked off

1866
03:04:07.049 --> 03:04:09.540
and all their estates went to the Emperors.

1867
03:04:09.651 --> 03:04:12.620
Unless they went home
and killed themselves.

1868
03:04:12.821 --> 03:04:15.016
then nothing happened.

1869
03:04:16.641 --> 03:04:18.002
And their families...

1870
03:04:18.127 --> 03:04:20.589
Their families were taken care of. Tom.

1871
03:04:22.364 --> 03:04:23.998
That was a good break.

1872
03:04:24.237 --> 03:04:25.782
a nice deal.

1873
03:04:26.368 --> 03:04:27.632
Yeah.

1874
03:04:28.756 --> 03:04:30.756
They went home...

1875
03:04:31.907 --> 03:04:34.375
...and sat in a hot bath...

1876
03:04:34.877 --> 03:04:36.782
...opened up their veins

1877
03:04:37.606 --> 03:04:39.706
 and bled to death.

1878
03:04:41.650 --> 03:04:45.379
And sometimes they had a
little party before they did it.

1879
03:04:50.993 --> 03:04:54.060
Don't worry about anything.
Frankie Five-Angels.

1880
03:04:54.797 --> 03:04:56.734
Thanks. Tom.

1881
03:04:56.758 --> 03:04:58.058
Thanks.

1882
03:05:16.485 --> 03:05:17.847
See you. Tom.

1883
03:05:17.920 --> 03:05:19.046
Addio. Frankie.

1884
03:05:30.799 --> 03:05:33.596
Kay. you have to go.

1885
03:05:35.471 --> 03:05:36.763
So pretty...

1886
03:05:36.772 --> 03:05:38.730
Kay. please hurry. He is coming.

1887
03:05:47.749 --> 03:05:48.979
Anthony...

1888
03:05:49.803 --> 03:05:51.603
Kiss Mama goodbye.

1889
03:05:54.089 --> 03:05:56.758
Anthony. would kiss your mother goodbye!

1890
03:05:57.259 --> 03:05:59.923
Anthony. say goodbye to Mama. Anthony...

1891
03:05:59.947 --> 03:06:01.647
I love you. Anthony.

1892
03:06:03.699 --> 03:06:05.228
Kay. please.

1893
03:06:08.904 --> 03:06:10.802
All right.

1894
03:06:23.552 --> 03:06:25.383
Mary. come here.

1895
03:06:33.095 --> 03:06:34.991
Anthony...

1896
03:06:35.015 --> 03:06:37.015
Anthony. please. Kiss me once.

1897
03:08:17.332 --> 03:08:18.996
Easy.

1898
03:08:24.973 --> 03:08:27.542
Anthony! Anthony!

1899
03:08:28.076 --> 03:08:30.044
He is here. we're going fishing.

1900
03:08:30.212 --> 03:08:33.649
No! Michael wants to take him to Reno now.

1901
03:08:34.816 --> 03:08:36.206
Shit!

1902
03:08:37.953 --> 03:08:41.154
Okay. kid. you gotta
go to Reno with your pop.

1903
03:08:42.424 --> 03:08:43.789
Come on. Anthony.

1904
03:08:43.813 --> 03:08:45.712
I'll take you fishing tomorrow. okay?

1905
03:08:49.097 --> 03:08:50.221
That a boy.

1906
03:08:50.232 --> 03:08:52.297
Anthony... Listen.

1907
03:08:52.806 --> 03:08:55.006
I'll catch one for you with the secret.

1908
03:08:55.230 --> 03:08:57.130
All right?
Okay.

1909
03:08:59.441 --> 03:09:01.206
Okay. Al. let's go.

1910
03:09:40.615 --> 03:09:43.183
Mr Roth. you understand I
have to take you into custody?

1911
03:09:43.185 --> 03:09:44.743
Yes. I understand.

1912
03:09:44.853 --> 03:09:47.877
Could you give us your reaction
to the High Court of Israel's ruling.

1913
03:09:48.056 --> 03:09:50.786
I'm a retired investor on a pension.

1914
03:09:51.059 --> 03:09:54.556
I went to Israel because I
wished to live there as a Jew.

1915
03:09:54.930 --> 03:09:56.457
in the twilight of my life.

1916
03:10:02.604 --> 03:10:05.530
Frankie! Come on out.
let's play some Hearts.

1917
03:10:14.382 --> 03:10:15.974
Frankie!

1918
03:10:31.700 --> 03:10:34.631
Is it true you're worth over
300 million dollars. Mr Roth?

1919
03:10:35.070 --> 03:10:38.006
I'm a retired investor.
living on a pension.

1920
03:10:38.640 --> 03:10:42.303
I came home to vote in
the presidential election.

1921
03:10:42.410 --> 03:10:44.878
because they wouldn't give
me an absentee ballot.

1922
03:10:58.293 --> 03:11:00.488
Jesus Christ.

1923
03:11:01.696 --> 03:11:04.461
Hail Mary. full of grace.

1924
03:11:05.066 --> 03:11:06.693
The Lord is with thee.

1925
03:11:07.435 --> 03:11:10.563
Blessed art thou amongst women.

1926
03:11:11.006 --> 03:11:14.339
Blessed is the fruit of thy womb. Jesus.

1927
03:11:15.577 --> 03:11:20.605
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners.

1928
03:12:01.389 --> 03:12:04.223
Hey! Everybody. come on.
pay attention. Come here.

1929
03:12:05.327 --> 03:12:06.992
This is my friend Carlo Rizzi.

1930
03:12:07.329 --> 03:12:08.762
This is my brother Fredo.

1931
03:12:08.864 --> 03:12:12.165
You know Fredo sure don't you.
This is my stepbrother Tom.

1932
03:12:12.434 --> 03:12:14.994
and that's his girl Theresa.

1933
03:12:15.170 --> 03:12:17.404
This cute little thing over
here is my sister Connie.

1934
03:12:17.428 --> 03:12:18.639
I was telling you about her.

1935
03:12:18.640 --> 03:12:20.335
Come on. say hello to Carlo.

1936
03:12:20.475 --> 03:12:22.275
He is good-looking. ain't he?
Yes.

1937
03:12:23.311 --> 03:12:25.836
The droopy thing over there.
that's my brother Mike.

1938
03:12:26.014 --> 03:12:27.911
We call him Joe Collars.
You know what I mean.

1939
03:12:27.949 --> 03:12:31.476
Come on. Sit down.
Talk to each other.

1940
03:12:31.920 --> 03:12:33.353
Hey. Mr Einstein...

1941
03:12:37.525 --> 03:12:39.993
Here is the cake.
Sally. get in here!

1942
03:12:40.161 --> 03:12:42.026
I was scared.
Come on.

1943
03:12:43.098 --> 03:12:44.256
Where is your father?

1944
03:12:44.266 --> 03:12:46.496
We sent him on a wild goose chase.
Christmas shopping.

1945
03:12:46.601 --> 03:12:47.993
Let's see that thing.

1946
03:12:50.105 --> 03:12:51.800
That's nice!

1947
03:12:52.540 --> 03:12:54.505
Should I put the candles on now?
Yeah. go on.

1948
03:12:54.509 --> 03:12:56.333
You help her. All right. Carlo.
Sure.

1949
03:12:57.812 --> 03:12:59.004
What is that? Rum?

1950
03:12:59.080 --> 03:13:00.374
Yeah. Boy that's good

1951
03:13:05.720 --> 03:13:08.780
Sonny. come on! Don't touch
the antipasto till Pop sees it.

1952
03:13:09.224 --> 03:13:10.452
He is not ugly...

1953
03:13:17.365 --> 03:13:19.629
Say. what do you think of
the nerve of those Japs?

1954
03:13:19.653 --> 03:13:21.001
Those slanty eyed bastards

1955
03:13:21.002 --> 03:13:23.400
dropping bombs in out back
yard and on Pop's birthday.

1956
03:13:23.405 --> 03:13:26.602
They didn't know it was Pop's birthday.

1957
03:13:27.108 --> 03:13:29.703
We shoul've expected
it after the oil embargo.

1958
03:13:29.727 --> 03:13:30.811
What do you mean expect it?

1959
03:13:30.812 --> 03:13:32.504
 Expect it or not. they've
got no right dropping bombs!

1960
03:13:32.547 --> 03:13:34.581
What are you? A Jap-lover or
something? Are you on their side?

1961
03:13:34.649 --> 03:13:36.842
I understand 30.000 men
enlisted this morning.

1962
03:13:36.918 --> 03:13:38.180
Bunch of saps.

1963
03:13:38.320 --> 03:13:39.651
Why are they saps?

1964
03:13:39.821 --> 03:13:42.014
Sonny. come on. We do
not talk about the war.

1965
03:13:42.023 --> 03:13:44.423
Hey beat it! You go
talk to Carlo. Right?

1966
03:13:47.885 --> 03:13:50.410
They are saps because they
risk their lives for strangers.

1967
03:13:50.432 --> 03:13:51.524
Now that's Pop talking.

1968
03:13:51.599 --> 03:13:53.790
You're goddamn right. Mike.
that's Pop talking!

1969
03:13:53.935 --> 03:13:55.969
They risk their lives for their country.

1970
03:13:55.971 --> 03:13:57.936
Your country isn't your blood.
You remember that.

1971
03:13:58.006 --> 03:13:59.398
I don't feel that way.

1972
03:13:59.422 --> 03:14:02.641
Well if you don't fell that way.
why don't you just quit collage

1973
03:14:02.665 --> 03:14:03.944
and go to join the Army.

1974
03:14:03.945 --> 03:14:05.248
I did.

1975
03:14:06.247 --> 03:14:08.147
I enlisted in the Marines.

1976
03:14:11.486 --> 03:14:13.780
Mikey. why didn't you come to us?

1977
03:14:14.289 --> 03:14:15.415
What do you mean?

1978
03:14:15.490 --> 03:14:17.982
I mean Pop had to pull a lot of
strings to get you a deferment.

1979
03:14:18.006 --> 03:14:19.593
I didn't ask for it.

1980
03:14:19.794 --> 03:14:21.662
I didn't ask for a deferment.
I didn't want it.

1981
03:14:22.797 --> 03:14:25.166
What is wrong?
Come on! Knock it off!

1982
03:14:25.934 --> 03:14:26.958
Punk!

1983
03:14:27.402 --> 03:14:29.730
Sonny. sit down.
Go on.

1984
03:14:32.474 --> 03:14:34.743
Mommy. Daddy is fighting again!

1985
03:14:39.214 --> 03:14:40.977
Go show Carlo the tree.

1986
03:14:45.000 --> 03:14:46.800
Go ahead! Uncle Michael. Mamma.

1987
03:14:52.113 --> 03:14:53.442
Nice.

1988
03:14:55.497 --> 03:14:56.894
Nice.

1989
03:14:57.618 --> 03:15:00.118
Break your father's
heart on his birthday.

1990
03:15:01.636 --> 03:15:04.264
That's swell. Mike. Congratulations.

1991
03:15:04.439 --> 03:15:05.901
Don't encourage him!

1992
03:15:06.474 --> 03:15:09.374
Go on. get me a drink. Go on!

1993
03:15:13.681 --> 03:15:16.450
Mike. you don't understand
your father has plans for you.

1994
03:15:16.818 --> 03:15:19.785
Many times he and I have
talked about your future.

1995
03:15:22.991 --> 03:15:25.452
Talked to my father about my future?

1996
03:15:27.996 --> 03:15:29.361
My future.

1997
03:15:29.531 --> 03:15:32.261
Mikey. he has high hopes for you.

1998
03:15:32.434 --> 03:15:34.902
I have my own plans for my future.

1999
03:15:35.270 --> 03:15:38.134
Did you go to college to get 
stupid? You are really stupid.

2000
03:15:38.206 --> 03:15:39.671
He is here! Come on.

2001
03:15:42.043 --> 03:15:44.068
Come on.

2002
03:15:46.181 --> 03:15:47.705
Stupid!

2003
03:16:05.467 --> 03:16:07.731
Surprise!

2004
03:16:08.556 --> 03:16:12.525
For he is a jolly good fellow.
For he is a jolly good fellow

2005
03:16:16.698 --> 03:16:21.001
That nobody can deny.
Nobody can deny...

2006
03:16:22.500 --> 03:16:26.500
